title: vegetable beef biscuit bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: easy fruit pie
directions: Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer 1:
Mix 1 stick butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Press in cake pan.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, reserving 1 cup of the syrup; set aside.
Combine gelatin, boiling water and sugar.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add cold water, reserved pineapple syrup and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add cranberries, celery, nuts, orange zest and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into 6-cup mold. Chill until set.
Remove from mold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy rice pudding(microwave)
directions: Make pudding according to package directions.
Mix in raisins and rice until well blended.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Cover. Microwave on High for 2 minutes, rotating dish after first minute.
Serve warm or cold.

title: goli-she-was
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt, onion and green pepper.
Add milk to form a rather stiff batter.
It should be about the consistency of dumplings, stiff enough to barely drop from the spoon.
Add enough potatoes to double mixture.
Drop by teaspoons into 375° fat and fry until golden brown.
Drain and serve hot.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Cook potatoes in oil in skillet, but do not brown, adding the oil as it is needed.
Lift out potatoes with a slotted spoon and arrange in buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter and season with salt and pepper.
Cook burger in same skillet; drain.
Add the sauce to beef; mix thoroughly and heat.
Pour meat mixture over the potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. During last 5 minutes of cooking, remove and sprinkle on cheese.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain and cut artichokes into pieces. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Grease a pie pan or quiche dish.
Pour all ingredients in and sprinkle with garlic powder. Cook for 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers and enjoy!

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine
cup
melted
butter,
pepper, sour cream, cheese, salt, onion and soup.
Blend and pour over potatoes in a 3 quart casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter and
sprinkle
on
top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box, adding softened butter.
Bake in a 17 x 11 1/2-inch jelly pan or a large cookie sheet with sides, at 350° for 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Combine the milk, sugar, marshmallows and coconut in a saucepan, until marshmallows are melted.
Spread over cake.
In a saucepan, cook remaining ingredients over low heat.
Spread over the coconut layer.
Refrigerate.
Makes 30 servings.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Beat in bananas.
Gradually add the dry ingredients, beating just until combined.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into 3 greased 5 3/4 x 3 x 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire rack.
Yield: 3 mini loaves.

title: beef loaf
directions: Saute onion in salad oil.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Pack into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil, then strain.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple in pan.
Cover with cherries.
Cover with cake mix and top with nuts.
Cut margarine in pieces and put over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Fry beef and onion until browned.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in greased pie plate. Top with chillies.
Beat milk, baking powder, Bisquick and egg until smooth.
Pour over hamburger mixture.
Bake until done (25 minutes or more).
Take out of oven and top with cubed tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted. Serve hot topped with shredded lettuce, olives and sour cream.
Makes a whole meal.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan and stir with a fork until blended, about 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: chocolate dipped peanut butter cookies(makes about 5 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla extract until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape in 1-inch balls. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Partially dip cookies into candy coating.
Place on wax paper lined baking sheet and stand until firm.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off excess fat.
In a 2-quart casserole, mix SpaghettiOs, cream of mushroom soup, onion and bacon.
Add ground beef and stir to mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.
It's ready to go!
Good with a green salad.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: Place pea pods and pineapple in crock-pot.
Stir together cornstarch and sugar.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water and add pineapple juice, soy sauce and ginger.
Bring to boil and cook for 1 minute.
Blend sauce into pea pods and pineapple.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: beef burritos
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add taco sauce to meat.
Spoon meat on tortillas.
Roll and place in pan.
Mix sour cream, soup and chiles.
Spread over tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey schnitzel
directions: In small shallow plate, combine egg whites and mustard.
Blend well and set aside.
Place bread crumbs on shallow plate; one at a time dip each cutlet first into egg mixture, then bread crumbs, coating both sides.
In medium skillet, heat 1 teaspoon oil; add cutlets.
Cook over medium-high heat until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining oil; turn cutlets.
Cook until golden brown, about 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: primavera linguini(simply delicious)
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and flour.
Stir in the soup mix and blend all with milk.
Bring to a boil and simmer, stirring occasionally until sauce is thickened and vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Toss sauce with hot linguini and add more Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Mix Cheddar and cream cheese until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Mold into bell or ball shapes.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with pimiento strips, spread on Triscuits.
Makes 12 balls.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Chop up tomatoes.
Mix in saucepan tomatoes, tomato paste, parsley flakes, sugar, salt, basil, garlic and oregano.
Heat to boiling.
Stir occasionally. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: super z ice cream sundaes
directions: For each serving, place scoops of ice cream in sundae dish. Serve with topping.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish with coconut, chopped nuts or sprinkles, if desired.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: louisiana sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell (9-inch); bake one hour at 350°.
Garnish with finely chopped pecans.
Serve warm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add Cavender's seasoning, soups, cheese and milk.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add diced chicken and spaghetti.
Simmer until warm throughout.
For extra spice add 1 can of Rotel.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers and combine all the other ingredients.
Mix with crackers and refrigerate overnight.

title: sauerkraut and noodles
directions: Saut sauerkraut, mushrooms and onions in butter until lightly browned.
Stir in boiled noodles and browned kielbasa. Serves 8 to 10 people as a side dish.

title: peanut butter chip chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large mixer bowl. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; blend in.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing to wire rack.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: rice salad
directions: Put on lettuce halves and top with boiled eggs and paprika. You may also add any type of meat, ham, chicken, tuna or bacon bits.
This is very good hot or cold.

title: bean salad
directions: Slice chestnuts and mix all ingredients.
Mix 1/2 cup oil, 1/2 cup vinegar, 3/4 cup sugar and salt and pepper (to taste).
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight.

title: world war i fruit cake
directions: Boil margarine, sugar, water, raisins and spices together for 3 to 4 minutes.
Cool.
Mix dry ingredients and add to the cooled mixture.
(Optional:
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup nuts or coconut.)

title: marshmallow fudge brownies and icing
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan 20 minutes at 350°.
Take from oven and put marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 3 minutes. Spread until top is covered with marshmallows.
Let cool.
Frost with icing.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Form into 40 bite size meatballs using a full teaspoon for each.
Brown meatballs lightly in vegetable oil.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat. Combine chili sauce and grape jelly.
Pour over meatballs.
Heat, stirring occasionally until jelly is melted.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes until sauce has thickened.
Baste occasionally.
Makes 40 appetizers.

title: mushroom rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chili
directions: In a dutch oven over medium heat, cook beef, onion and green pepper until meat is no longer pink.
Drain.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Cut fish into serving pieces.
Stir salt into milk.
Dip fish in milk and coat with crumbs.
Place fish in greased oblong pan.
Pour butter over fish and place pan on middle rack of oven.
Cook uncovered at 500° for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: In sauce pan, melt cheese, soup, milk, onion, oleo and worcestershire sauce.
Cook broccoli as directed and then drain. Combine broccoli, ham, rice to cheese mixture. Cook at 350 for 1 - 1 1/2 hours.

title: low cholesterol-low fat chili
directions: Brown meat in pan.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, crushed tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce, soy sauce and chili powder. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: big john's steamed shrimp
directions: Combine Old Bay, salt and pepper in small bowl.
In a steamer, combine water and vinegar; bring to a boil and place a layer of shrimp.
Sprinkle generously with seasonings.
Repeat process for approximately 3 layers of shrimp.
Steam for 8 to 10 minutes. Stir gently; cover again until tender.
Peel and eat!
Serve with cocktail sauce and lemon wedges.

title: howard glenn's sourdough bread
directions: Dump all ingredients in a bowl.

Measure 6 cups bromated bread flour and sift into mixture. Stir ingredients with a large spoon until a stiff batter is formed. Spray a large bowl with cooking spray and place dough therein. Cover with Saran Wrap and let rise on counter overnight.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Cream together butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla and flour, mixing well.
Spread evenly in buttered 9-inch round cake pan.
Place apple wedges into cake batter to form a circular pattern.
Mix together 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: potato salad from ireland
directions: Cook potatoes in skins until done. Drain and cube.
Toss other ingredients gently and stir in potatoes.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Form meat, egg and onion in loaf and cook until done at 275°.

title: stacie's fruit on a stick
directions: Take fruit balls and arrange them in your own way on bamboo skewers.
Chill in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar and eggs.
Blend in oil.
Stir together soda, salt, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Mix and blend.
Add carrots. Bake in three 8-inch square or three 9-inch round pans at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Insert toothpick for testing; if comes out clean, cake is done.

title: sunny sipper
directions: In a 4 cup glass measure, stir together all ingredients. Cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High 3 minutes or until boiling. Makes about 2 cups or 2 servings.

title: simple macaroni salad
directions: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente. Drain and rinse with cold water until no longer hot. Transfer noodles to a large bowl. Stir in red and green bell peppers, green onions, celery and olive oil. Mix in mayonnaise and soup mix. Mix well. Refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, stir soup and soy sauce.
Mix in 1/2 can onions, pepper and green beans.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Add rest of onions and cook 5 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, coconut, flour, vanilla, salt and milk.
Pour in uncooked pie shell and bake at 350° until done.

title: fettucini with parsley
directions: Cook fettucini noodles according to package directions; drain well.
Add next 5 ingredients and toss well until noodles are well coated.
Add Parmesan cheese and toss gently.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; slice into 1/4-inch pieces.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Put a layer of potato slices; brush with melted butter, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, pepper and salt.
Put another layer of potatoes in; follow directions for first layer.
Continue layering until all potatoes are used.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, until a fork will go through easily, about 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Trim excess fat from chicken and twist the tip of the chicken wing under.
Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Italian salad dressing mix.
Roll each piece of chicken first in butter mixture, then in potato flakes on wax paper.
Arrange in a single layer on several aluminum foil lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Saute mushroom stems in butter.
Combine mushroom stems with all the other ingredients, adding breadcrumbs until desired consistency.
Stuff caps and bake on a cookie sheet for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Let sit for 5 minutes before serving.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes, but do not peel.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices and coat with next 4 ingredients (mixed well).
Arrange slices in a greased baking dish.
Dot with margarine and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: skillet chicken and wild rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in 10-inch skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Prepare according to directions on back of box.
Make into three layers.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together the sour cream, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla, then add fruit cocktail, pineapple and nuts.
Freeze.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas, together in a bowl. Spread mixture over uncooked flour tortillas. Roll tortilla tightly.
Slice into 1-inch thick bite size pieces.

title: good salad
directions: Layer in the order given.

title: taco soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown meat and onion; drain.
Puree tomatoes in their liquid; add to pan with sauce, water, beans, corn and seasoning.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Can top each serving with chopped tomatoes, shredded Cheddar cheese, sour cream and corn chips.

title: wassail
directions: Stick cloves in orange.
Place in juice and simmer for 6 hours.

title: boston baked beans(serves 12)
directions: In heavy 4 to 5-quart casserole, bring 2 quarts of water to a boil over high heat.
Drop in the dried beans and boil them for about 2 minutes.
The water should cover the beans by at least 2-inches.
Add more if necessary.
Turn off the heat and let the beans soak for 1 hour, then add the peeled onion and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Bring to a boil again.
Reduce the heat to low; partially cover the pan and simmer for about 1 hour or until the beans are tender.
Check from time to time and add more boiling water to the pot, if necessary.
(The beans should be covered with water throughout the cooking.)
Drain the beans through a fine sieve set over a bowl.
Pick out and discard the onion.
Reserve the cooking liquid.
There should be about 2 quarts of liquid; add water if necessary.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter and sugar in bottom of pan.
Bake 5 minutes.
Save 1/4 of mixture for the top.
Mix lemon juice, cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Mix jello and water.
Let cool.
Add lemon juice mixture to jello.
Beat Milnot until stiff. Fold all ingredients together into crust.
Sprinkle top with remaining graham crackers.
Chill for at least 4 hours.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring to a full boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir together.
Drop by heaping teaspoons on wax paper and let cook.
Mixture hardens quickly so you must work fast.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a skillet, cook beef with onion until brown, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Heat through, stirring often.
Serve on buns.

title: jim's best oatmeal chippers
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Add and cream the brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to butter and sugar; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda to mixture; beat well.
Add oats and chocolate chips to mixture; combine well.

title: mexican potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes until just soft. Cool and quarter. Toss in the remaining ingredients and mix well. Serve immediately at room temperature or refrigerate.

title: preston's mama's tomato pie
directions: Brown pie shell; let cool.
Place ham or bacon on bottom of pie shell, followed by sliced tomatoes and onion.
Make 2 tiers of meat, tomatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Mix grated cheese and mayonnaise together; spread on top of pie. Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until cheese is melted and browned.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes and almonds. Sprinkle them over the top of the casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, or until browned lightly.

title: crisp chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce. Great in hot weather; simple and refreshing.

title: lazy man's stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together and season as you wish. Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with half of cabbage.
Layer ground beef mixture on top.
Then cover with remaining cabbage. Mix the two soups and pour over the top.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: southwest spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Whisk together the milk and egg; mix in the hot pasta. Spread the mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook the pork, onion, green pepper and garlic together in a large skillet for about 6 minutes over medium heat, until the pork is cooked through.
Drain or spoon off excess fat.
Stir the chili powder, cumin, oregano, salt and black pepper into the pork and cook for about 2 minutes.
Stir in the tomato sauce and cook for 2 minutes more.

title: green beans with new potatoes
directions: Wash beans twice or three times.

Place in kettle. Cover with water and put in the salt pork and bacon grease (about 3 tablespoons). Cook about 3/4 hour. Scrub the potatoes and put on top of the beans. Cook until the potatoes are tender.

title: no fat italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill for an hour.
Makes 12 servings. 2 Tbsp. 9 calories.
Fat:
0 gms., Fat 0%.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk for 2 minutes.
After done boiling, add peanut butter and marshmallow; beat until mixed.
Add oatmeal and vanilla; mix all together.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Sift both the sugar and flour before measuring.
Sift the flour 4 times after measuring.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage and ground round. Boil shrimp in shrimp boil. Stir in 2 1/2 cups of water and 2 (6 ounce) boxes of Zatarains jambalaya mix. Bring to a boil; stir. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 25 minutes. Stir occasionally. Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes. Stir in sausage, shrimp (peeled) and 1/2 jar of Pace picante sauce.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Blend in milk alternately with flour and flavoring.
Blend in flavoring.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans at 350°.

title: 3 day dill pickles
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Place dill, garlic, onion and hot pepper in bottom of a quart jar.
Place cucumbers in jar.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over cucumbers and seal.
Set in sun for 3 days.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: In large bowl, toss cabbage, onion, carrots, green pepper and pickles.
Add red pepper, salt and sugar; mix well.
Mix ketchup and vinegar together; pour over vegetables.
This is better if it is made the night before.
Keeps forever in the refrigerator.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: creation crunch
directions: Have children combine various foods in small bowls to create their own "Creation Crunch."
As kids create, affirm them for their God-given creativity because they're made in God's image.

title: fruit salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise with cream cheese; add whipping cream.
Then add all other ingredients.
Also, nuts may be added.
Chill.

title: caramels
directions: In a 3-quart heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture reaches firm ball stage (244°), stirring occasionally.
Add butter and gradually add milk so mixture does not stop boiling.
Stirring constantly, cook rapidly to firm ball stage again.
Remove from heat, add vanilla flavoring and pour mixture into buttered 9-inch square baking dish without scraping the sides of the saucepan.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Makes 81 caramels (1 x 1-inch).

title: chicken wings in oyster sauce
directions: Boil mixture until thick.
Pour over cooked wings. Enjoy.

title: "miss pat's" brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Check by sticking a cake tester in it.
Take out of the oven and put 15 large marshmallows on top.
Put back in oven just long enough to soften so you can spread them with a knife.
Spread filling on top.

title: deep south bread pudding
directions: Combine bread, milk and cream.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Add vanilla and spices.
Stir in butter and raisins.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Set in pan of warm water.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra, leaving short stems. Pack into ten clean, hot pint jars.
Place pod of pepper and one clove of garlic in each jar. Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over okra.
Seal jars.
Let stand for several weeks before using. Yields 10 pints.

title: easy chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: red wine vinaigrette
directions: Mix well.
Serve over cold cooked vegetables or fresh green salad.

title: dad's fruit delight
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour filling over pie crust.
Chill until set.
Put pie filling on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat egg in small bowl.
Add crackers, salt, evaporated milk and catsup.
In large bowl, mix beef with onion and pepper.
Mix in egg mixture.
Pat into loaf pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add 1 cup heated milk.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook until it bubbles.
Pour over vanilla wafers and banana slices.
Sprinkle with crushed vanilla wafers.
Let cool.
Serve and keep refrigerated.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Cook over low heat until 230° to 234° on candy thermometer. Add peanuts.
Stir constantly until thermometer reaches 290°. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread onto buttered pan; cool.
Break into pieces.

title: beef bourguignonne
directions: Mix together and bake covered for 3 hours at 350.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and whipped topping.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate until it sets.

title: kentucky cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cooled cornbread in oblong pan.
Layer onions, cucumbers, tomato, green pepper, kidney beans and black pepper. Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Spoon over top of beans, then sprinkle cheese on top of salad.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: summertime fruit slush
directions: Peel and seed fruit as needed.
Place an assortment of fruits in blender.
Add honey.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into 8 ounce plastic cups and place in freezer until slushy but not solid.
Eat with a spoon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
Stir lemon juice into pumpkin. Sift together dry ingredients.
Fold flour mixture into sugar and pumpkin mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn onto a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake together.
Unroll bread.
Spread with filling and roll again, making a pumpkin roll.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken ala kel
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, beat eggs and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients and mix well. Dip chicken tenders in eggs, then dredge in breadcrumb mixture, coating well.
Place chicken pieces on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all together and freeze in ice cream maker.

title: spanish beans
directions: Brown about a pound of ground chuck in small amount of oil. When meat is browned, add onion.
Let this cook for several minutes.
Next, add celery and bell pepper, then a can of tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Let these ingredients cook slowly for about 5 minutes.
At this point, if mixture is too juicy, it may be thickened by adding about a tablespoon of flour to make a smooth paste.
Add red kidney beans.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pattie's peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy. Beat in peanut butter and sugar. Slowly add milk into mixture, blending thoroughly. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into prepared graham cracker crust (optional: sprinkle with chopped nuts). Freeze until firm and serve.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine, and sugar.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla and walnut flavoring, coconut, and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9 inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs, butter, nuts, chips and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°. Test with a straw or toothpick to see if filling is set.

title: cinnamon bread sticks
directions: Cut crust off slices of bread.
Roll thin, then spread with the mixture of cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread on each slice as if you were putting on butter.
After you have spread on the mixture, roll the slice up and roll it in melted butter or margarine.
You then roll the stick in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Put each stick on baking pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until brown.
You can store in the freezer and use as needed.

title: tally ho tomato pudding
directions: For 10 minutes, boil the tomato puree, boiling water, brown sugar and salt.
Pour over the buttered bread cubes, in a buttered casserole.
Bake, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven in the casserole.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a bowl. Beat in eggs, salt and vanilla; mix well. Sift together soda and flour. Add to creamed mixture. Add bananas and nuts; mix well. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: how to make self-rising flour(one pound)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tightly covered container and use in any recipe calling for self-rising flour.

title: quick and easy hot rolls
directions: Melt margarine and set aside.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and margarine; mix and add flour.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Mash down.
Shape into rolls and let rise again, about 1 hour or more depending on temperature of room.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Brush with margarine when taken from oven.

title: six-layer bars
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs with melted butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with nuts, chocolate chips and coconut.
Pour milk over top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven (until lightly browned).
Cool; cut into bars.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Cook 5 hours at 300°.
Leave set 20 minutes and shred.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk; add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Add pineapple and oranges.
Cool for 1 hour.
Soften cheese; mix with salad dressing, Dream Whip and nuts.
Add to jello mixture.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Blend sugar and eggs together; add melted butter.
Add other ingredients as listed; mix.
Pour into 2 nine-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot cross buns
directions: The day before buns are to be baked, mix sugar with 1/2 c. melted butter. Add four of the egg yolks, well beaten and milk. Soften yeast in warm water; add to sugar mixture. Sift 4 c. flour with salt, nutmeg, and cloves; beat. In separate bowl, beat egg whites until frothy but not stiff; fold into the batter. Add raisins and candied fruit; stir. Add remaining flour, 1 c. at a time, until you have a soft dough. Place dough in oiled bowl; oil top of dough. Cover with a damp cloth and plastic wrap; store in warm place for 2 to 3 hours. Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: Peel
and
devein
shrimp;
combine
soy sauce, sherry, ketchup, sugar
and
pepper.
Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Add garlic;
stir-fry for 30 seconds;
remove garlic.
Add ginger; stir-fry for 30 seconds; add shrimp, stir-fry for 5 minutes or until shrimp
turn	pink.
Add onion, celery, mushrooms, water chestnuts and bamboo shoots.
Stir-fry 30 seconds; stir in soy sauce mixture.
Add pimento and pea pods; heat through.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients in a two quart saucepan.
Bring to boil and let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Place in covered dish and chill for several days, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve. Makes about four cups.

title: holiday sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add hot water and dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Stir in sweet potatoes, nuts and vanilla; beat well. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in 3 greased 8-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting with your choice of icing.

title: three "c" casserole(corn, crackers and cheese)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 cup casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
So delicious.

title: jennifer's apple crumble
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Grease the baking pan.
Put the sliced apples in a deep dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, sugar, cinnamon and ginger.
Mix together and pour into baking pan.
Mix the flour, butter and three-quarters cup of sugar until mixture crumbles.
Pat this mixture on top of the apples loosely.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Break eggs into casserole.
Beat slightly.
Mix in flour and sugar.
Add corn.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: boxcar children brownies(microwave)
directions: Add melted margarine, cocoa and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and pour into the baking dish. Cook in the microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes, turning 1/4 turn every 2 minutes.
When brownies are done, the top will look dry and spring back when touched.

title: cry babies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Add dry ingredients and hot water alternately with shortening mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly; add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Flavor with love and kindly service.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith. Blend well into daily living.
Bake well with warmth of human kindness.
Serve with a smile all the time.

title: baked bananas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange bananas in 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with raisins.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over bananas.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn casserole no. 2
directions: Drain corn and green beans.
Combine corn, green beans, celery soup and sour cream in mixing bowl.
Stir in minced onion.
Pour in casserole dish and top with Ritz crackers and shredded cheese.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: alf's special hot cakes
directions: Put eggs in bowl and whip until yellow and frothy.
Blend in sour cream and cottage cheese until smooth.
Add flour; mix until flour is blended.
Pour batter into hot skillet with melted butter.
Cook until golden brown.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 cups.

title: cheesy chicken breasts
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on a plate.
Beat egg and oil in a bowl.
Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, on a cookie sheet or baking pan, until tender and slightly browned.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes more to melt the cheese.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Premix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add nuts (optional).
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Lightly season chicken with seasoned salt (remove the skin and bones first).
Brown in a Dutch oven; add sherry.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove chicken to a serving dish.
Measure pan juices and add water to make 1 1/4 cups liquid. Blend liquid and gravy mix in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil and simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and blend in sour cream.
Pour over chicken.

title: salted pecans
directions: Place pecan halves in shallow pan with enough melted butter to moisten each half.
Place in moderate oven and toast until pecans are a light brown, then remove and salt.
Turn pecans often during toasting process so they will not burn.

title: medallions of pork tenderloin
directions: Dry meat with towels.
Combine salt, pepper and flour; dredge medallions.
Shake off excess.
Beat eggs with water.
Dip medallions in eggs and coat with bread crumbs.
Press meat with heel of palm to adhere bread crumbs; dry for 10 minutes.

title: all-in-one-dinner
directions: Mix ground chuck with onion soup mix and place on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put uncooked veggies over meat.
Mix sour cream, cheese, butter and soup together.
Mix with hash browns.
Place over veggies.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Salt to taste.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together, if mixture is too dry add about 1/8 cup milk. Make into walnut-sized balls. Freeze. Bake as needed at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks and part of milk to moisten.
Add milk gradually, cooking on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
When thick, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Let cool.
Line deep pan or dish with vanilla wafers, bottom and part of sides.
Cover with layer of bananas, layer of pudding, etc.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all together; roll in tiny balls, then roll in granulated sugar.
Place on baking sheet and bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan (layer).
Layer ingredients starting with the cherry pie filing, pineapple and juice, dry cake mix, coconut, oleo on top and chopped walnuts on top of the oleo.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: vanilla sand cookies
directions: Work all ingredients together with your hands until you have a smooth, stiff paste.
To form cookies, break off a small chunk, a spoonful.
Roll into a ball between the palms of your hands. Flatten into a round and you will have a circle with fine, cracked edges.
Arrange these on baking sheet and press a design in the top if you wish.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until golden in color.
They complement fresh fruit nicely.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and blend.
Sift dry ingredients.
Alternate dry ingredients with buttermilk into creamed mixture.
Fold in mashed bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or two greased 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with Butter Cream frosting.

title: nut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add nuts (flour nuts).
Beat all together. Pour into tube pan. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Grease one 9 x 13 pan. Arrange rhubarb in bottom of pan. Sprinkle dry gelatin over top. Sprinkle with sugar and then cake mix. Drizzle butter over top, followed by cold water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: festive salad
directions: Heat 1 1/3 cups juice until hot; dissolve jello in juice. When slightly thickened, add cream cheese.
Mix in fruit cocktail; fold in Cool Whip.
Put in mold and chill about 3 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add onions; cook until onions are transparent.
Add mushrooms, seasonings and thawed spinach. Cook until spinach is warmed through.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese; bake at 400° until cheese is bubbling.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Add a salad and French bread.
Ummm!!!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs in boiler; add flour, then add small amounts of sugar and milk, beating each time by hand until all lumps are out. Then add chocolate.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens; remove from heat and add butter, salt and vanilla.
Pour in a baked pie crust.
Whip egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy; add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over pie and brown top under broiler.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil hen; debone and cut into small pieces.
Put fat in pan.
Add

title: blueberry loaf
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla on low speed for 1 minute. Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat 15 seconds on low, then 45 more seconds on medium speed.
Stir in nuts and blueberries.
Spread batter in greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme; mix until well blended. Serve with fresh fruit and cookies as dippers. Yields 2 cups.

title: caramel topping
directions: Boil in pan for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Keep water over can. Makes an excellent topping for sliced apples or use on ice cream.

title: spiced orange juice
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes, then chill.
Just before serving, strain this mixture into punch bowl or pitcher.
Add orange juice concentrate and ginger ale.

title: microwave cheese pastry snacks
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together cheese, flour, cereal, walnuts, garlic salt, butter, bacon and water with a fork until a dough forms.
Drop 7 level tablespoons in a circle onto each of 3 lightly buttered plates suitable for microwave.
(Butter plates only around edges, where dough will be placed.)
Sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave one plate at a time at High for 2 3/4 to 3 1/4 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn after 1 1/2 minutes.
Dough will be slightly puffed when done and will be crisp on drying.
Remove immediately from plate.
Serve hot or cold.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Makes 21 snacks.

title: southern tea
directions: Steep tea bags in 2 cups boiling water for 1 minute. Combine in gallon pitcher and add enough water and ice to fill completely.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown meat and garlic in skillet and drain fat.
Blend next 3 ingredients in a bowl; stir in meat/garlic. Boil stuffing shells according to directions on package; drain.
Fill each shell with cheese/meat mixture.
Place in a baking pan; cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Brown meat well in round frying pan or wok.
When done add Worcestershire and soy sauces and all the vegetables.
Cook for about 10 to 15 minutes and add teriyaki sauce.
(You may add more teriyaki than recipe calls for.)
When done, serve over rice or pasta.
M-mmm good!

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, flour, baking powder and sugar; mix well.
Add corn. Gradually add milk. Pour into well-buttered dish and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pot roast
directions: Flour roast on both sides, then brown in frying pan.
Put roast and all the other ingredients into crock-pot (6-quart size if possible).
Start the night before or cook the standard 8 to 9 hours.
Cook on medium or low.

title: alice's new england clam chowder
directions: Drain and reserve clam liquid.
Add enough water to clam liquid to make 2 cups.
Fry bacon of pork until crisp.
Remove bacon or pork and crumble and set aside.
Saute onions in bacon grease for about 5 minutes, drain and add to potatoes and simmer in clam liquid until thick.
(I use a masher and slightly mash potatoes to make them thicken)
It should be fairly thick.
Add approx. 2 Tbsp. of the bacon grease to the chowder.
Add clams, cream, salt & pepper & butter.
Reheat, but do not boil.
Top with crumbled bacon or salt pork and serve.
Makes about 2 1/2 to 3 quarts.

title: turkey divan with peaches
directions: Simmer turkey in an inch of water for 15 to 20 minutes until the pieces are no longer pink.
Cook broccoli to package directions without salt.
In small bowl, stir together the sour cream, mayonnaise, onion powder and garlic powder.
Spray shallow baking pan with nonstick spray.
Add turkey; arrange broccoli and peach halves around tenderloins.
Spoon sour cream mixture on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 6 to 7-inches from heat for 5 to 6 minutes or until the sour cream mixture is puffy and light brown.

title: biscuits and gravy
directions: Brown turkey sausage.
Add water and chopped onion.
Blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Serve on refrigerator biscuits.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Melt cheese in Ro-Tel.
Add chicken and mushroom soup and onion.

title: homemade pancake batter
directions: Beat egg with hand beater or whip until fluffy.
Mix in remaining just until smooth.
For thinner pancakes, add 1/4 cup milk.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: Cut Velveeta into small pieces.
Microwave approximately 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir.
Add 1/2 to 1 whole can of chili, depending on taste.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: spanakopita(greek spinach pie)
directions: Brown onion in olive oil.
Put browned onion in bowl with spinach (well drained), eggs and cheeses.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper (if you like), dill and parsley.
Melt butter.
Brush 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Layer filo dough one sheet at a time, buttering each one.
Put 10 sheets down.
Spread spinach mixture. Cover with 10 more sheets of filo brushing each one with butter. With razor blade or sharp knife, cut through top 10 sheets to cut into pieces.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: almond-spinach casserole(my own concoction)
directions: Thaw spinach; drain.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet. Saute almonds; set almonds aside.
In same skillet, saute celery and onion until golden brown (you might need to add another tablespoon of butter).
Dilute 1 can soup with 1/3 cup water in which bouillon cube has been dissolved.
Add to sauteed vegetables.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix 1/2 of the soup mixture with spinach.
Mix remaining soup
mixture with rice.
Pour spinach mixture into buttered baking dish.
Pour over this the rice mixture.
Sprinkle toasted almonds on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.
Casserole can be prepared in advance.
Freezes well.

title: peanut kiss cookies
directions: Add egg and vanilla to the first 4 ingredients.
Blend in the flour.
Shape into balls and roll in white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out and add chocolate kisses.
Press into cookies.
Bake for 3 minutes longer.

title: creamy chip dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix other ingredients together until fluffy.
Add a large bottle or bag of Armour dried beef that is finely chopped.

title: chocolate mint bars
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in saucepan.
Beat eggs and sugar well and add chocolate mixture to this.
Add flour, vanilla, salt and chopped walnuts to mixture.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.
When cool, frost with Peppermint Frosting.

title: buttery pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; butter and eggs should be room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Beat on high speed for 20 minutes; scrape sides with a rubber spatula.
Grease well bottom only of tube pan (angel cake pan).
Line bottom with wax paper; put into cold oven.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Use cake tester; ovens vary.
If tester comes out clean, it's done.

title: baked chocolate pudding
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients including sugar.
Add milk, melted shortening and well beaten eggs.
Mix well; pour in a greased mold, cover and bake near center of oven until dinner is done.
Serve hot with Chocolate Sauce.
This pudding may be steamed, if desired.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Place chicken in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add peas and mixed vegetables.
Combine soup and broth in a saucepan and bring to a boil; pour over chicken.
Next, combine butter, salt, pepper and flour in a saucepan; heat on medium and then add buttermilk. Stir together well.
Spoon over top of pie and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy fettucini alfredo
directions: In a large saucepan combine cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, butter and milk.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add fettucini and toss lightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetables on baked potatoes
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Saute bell pepper, onion and broccoli, until onion is clear.
Divide in half and put on each potato.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into small balls.
Dip in waxed chocolate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken in French dressing for several hours; drain well.
Combine with other ingredients.
Serves 4.

title: classic cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool some (5 minutes).
Put cream cheese, cucumbers and onion in blender; blend until bottom of blender is clean.
Add other ingredients and beat until mixed.
Add dissolved Jell-O.
Mix.
Pour into ring mold or any Jello mold.
Chill until firm.
Garnish to suit the meal.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together with electric mixer, except shrimp.
Fold shrimp in by hand.
Refrigerate until serving time. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: green bean casserole(low-fat recipe)
directions: In an 8 or 9-inch glass pie plate, microwave liquid Butter Buds or chicken broth, wheat germ, oatmeal, Italian seasoning and garlic powder on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir after each minute. Remove mixture from pie plate; set aside.
In the same plate, combine beans, mushrooms and onion.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Stir in combined sour cream and cornstarch, coating vegetables thoroughly.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened; stir. Sprinkle reserved wheat germ mixture over the top before serving. Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate cake icing
directions: Boil until thicken, 3-4 minutes.
Punch holes in cake and ice while still warm.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix fruit and flour together.
Add other ingredients, adding milk last.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 20-25 minutes or until light brown.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil
chicken
and debone.
Cut up meat in skillet with tablespoon of butter or oil.
Cook onion, pepper, both cans of soup,
tomatoes and chili powder.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add chicken
meat.
In	9
x
13-inch
pan,
pour crushed chips in bottom.
Pour
chicken soup mixture on top of chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dump pie
directions: Dump pie filling in a 9 x 12-inch glass pan.
Spread pineapple over it.
Top with dry cake mix.
Chop up margarine and place evenly on top.
Sprinkle nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden on top.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a gallon jug. Use only enough oil to fill gallon. Mix well.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine; add brown sugar. Let cool; add eggs, flour and vanilla. Mix well. Mix in chips and pecans. Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Be sure not to overbake!

title: spinach dip(microwave)
directions: To defrost spinach, place packages in oven. Microwave at High for 5 minutes, turning packages over after half the cooking time. Let stand for 5 minutes. Drain thoroughly; set aside. Place soup mix and water in a small bowl. Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave at High for 1 minute. Let stand, covered, until vegetables are rehydrated. Place cream cheese in large bowl. Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until cream cheese is softened. Mix in rehydrated soup mix, drained spinach, sour cream and red pepper sauce. If desired, serve with sour dough or French bread cubes, carrot sticks or crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: italian crescent meat casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In frypan, brown ground chuck and onion; drain.
Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce; heat until hot and bubbly.
Combine cheese and sour cream.
Pour hot meat mixture into greased 12 x 8-inch or 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon cheese mixture over meat.

title: chinese style rice
directions: Scramble egg in oil in saucepan, stirring to break into pieces.
Add water, soy sauce, garlic and onions. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice and mushrooms. Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork before serving.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients like pie crust.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup; add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to crust mixture.
Roll out 1/2 of crust to fit large cookie sheet.
Put crushed cornflakes over it.
Fill with sliced apples.
Sprinkle the sugar and cinnamon over the apples.
Roll out the other 1/2 of the crust.
Put over the top and pinch edges together.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Spread over top of crust.
Do not add sugar to egg whites.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and pour following glaze while hot.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Add soup to onions.
Heat.
Slice cheese into soup and onion mixture.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli. Heat though.
Serve warm with doritos or nacho chips.

title: creole green beans
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in fat until onion is yellow. Blend in flour, add tomato juice gradually and cook for 5 minutes. Add beans and heat thoroughly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients; pour in casserole and top with bacon slices.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: zucchini-potato pancakes
directions: Whisk together milk and egg in medium size bowl.
Add the flour, baking powder, salt, pepper and garlic.
Whisk until smooth. Stir in the potatoes, zucchini, onion and cheese.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Using 1/4 cup for each pancake, cook until browned on underside, about 3 minutes.
Turn pancake over.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cook 5 minutes until cooked through.
Keep warm on plate.
Repeat. Makes 4 servings or 12 pancakes.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Put bread on bottom; add sausage.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: portobello-alfredo sauce
directions: Remove brown gills from undersides of mushroom caps using a spoon, and discard gills.
Chop mushrooms.
Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat; add mushrooms and garlic, and saute 5 to 6 minutes or until tender.
Stir in cream and milk.
Bring to a boil over medium high heat; reduce heat, and simmer, whisking constantly, 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese, pepper and salt; stir constantly until cheese melts and mixture thickens.
Stir in 2 Tbsp. parsley.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.

title: cheesy-broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package, omitting salt; drain well. Saute onion in butter in a medium saucepan.
Add broccoli and remaining ingredients to saucepan; cook over medium heat until cheese melts, stirring often.
Serve immediately.
Yields 5 1/2 cups.

title: beef chop suey
directions: Cook in pressure cooker on high until it steams well.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Turn off heat and let pressure go down. This could be cooked in a regular pan.
Should be cooked slow so rice won't stick.
This is good served with a fruit salad and rye bread.

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a large cookie sheet.
In a medium bowl with a fork mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. With a pastry blender cut in the margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
In a cup, beat eggs with a fork.
Reserve 1 tablespoon.
Put milk into remaining eggs and add this mixture to the flour mixture.
Blend until well mixed.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured board and roll with a floured rolling pin until dough is 1/2 inch thick.
With a knife, cut dough into 3-inch squares then cut each square into 2 triangles.
Place triangles 1 inch apart onto cookie sheet.
Brush with reserved egg and sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until golden.
Makes 10 to 12 scones.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in
ungreased
large
oblong glass baking dish. Cover bottom of pan thoroughly with chicken.
Pour soup over chicken.
Pour
broth
over soup.
Add drained vegetables over top.
Mix together
Bisquick
and milk.
Pour over top of vegetables.
Melt butter
and
pour
over mixture.
Don't stir any of this together.
Just
layer as instructed.
It mixes by itself. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake and debone chicken breasts and lay into a 15 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Prepare Stove Top according to directions. Spread on top of cubed chicken.
Mix 1 can water with chicken soup and celery soup and spread on top of Stove Top.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: ripe olive tuscan pot roast
directions: Brown beef in oil; add wine or bouillon and water to meat. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: mountaineer slaw
directions: Boil water, sugar and vinegar for 3 minutes; set aside to cool.
Toss shredded cabbage with salt; let set for 1 hour.
Then add remaining ingredients.
After liquid has cooled, pour over slaw mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 25 or more servings.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix all together except mushroom soup.
Roll in 1-inch balls. Line in roaster using all mixture.
Pour mushroom soup over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix all above except cheese and chilies.
Put half the batter in ungreased loaf pan; layer with chopped chilies, layer with cheese and add remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve with a spoon as a side dish with tacos.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth after removing fat.
Mix together with other ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place beans and soup into casserole dish and stir until well mixed.
Place mixture in oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle top of casserole with fried onions and bake until golden brown, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Mix well until sugar is melted.
Marinate meat in sauce for at least for 4 hours. Broil in oven until chicken is cooked thoroughly or grill on an outdoor grill.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix and make into patties and fry in oil.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a large Bundt pan. Cut biscuits in quarters.
Mix cinnamon and brown sugar. Roll biscuit quarters in mixture.
Drop into pan. Add sugar to melted butter and bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spicy chili(microwave)
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in a covered dish on full power for 8 to 10 minutes, or until all pink is gone.
Stir 1 to 2 times while cooking. Drain well.

title: taleroni
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Drain.
Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Add to noodles, then add all other ingredients. Place slices of cheese on top and heat until cheese is melted.

title: polish cabbage and ground beef
directions: Brown ground beef and drain the grease.
Add cabbage and simmer until cabbage is tender.
Add celery soup and milk.
Heat and serve.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Cook milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla 12 minutes or until thick.
Add coconut and nuts.

title: cocoa fudge pie
directions: Melt cocoa and butter together; add sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased pie plate at 325° until firm.

title: orange breakfast ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine orange peel, sugar and cream cheese.
Unroll both cans of rolls.
Press seams together to form a flat surface.
Spread with cream cheese.
Roll up as jelly roll, form a ring with roll and place on jelly roll pan.
From outside, cut halfway to center of ring all around ring, about 2 inches apart.
Give each piece a half turn.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar and orange juice.
Drizzle on top of ring.
Serve warm.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Put bread, buttered side up, in dish.
Sprinkle cooked sausage and cheese over buttered bread. Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Let stand 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator, covered. Take out of refrigerator 15 minutes before baking at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set.
Great for breakfast, brunch or anytime!

title: cinnamon baked apples
directions: Place apples in an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle with lemon juice. Toss to coat. Set aside.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Top with reserved
crumbs;
dot with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad-pretzel crust
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar. Spread mixture in 11 x 7 baking dish. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: shrimp casserole harpin
directions: Early in the day, cook shrimp as directed.
Place in 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with lemon juice and oil.
Cook rice as label directs; drain.
Refrigerate all.
About 1 hour and 10 minutes before serving, start heating oven to 350°.
In butter, saute green pepper and onion for 5 minutes.
Add to shrimp in casserole, along with rice and other ingredients, except 1/4 cup almonds and paprika.
Top with reserved almonds and sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, for 55 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss gently.
Makes 8 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: dessert kolachy
directions: Thoroughly blend margarine, softened cream cheese and sugar. Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Knead to form stiff dough; roll to 1/4-inch thickness on well-floured board.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Place 1/2 teaspoon preserves in center; press opposite corners together.
Place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from racks and cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice onions, sprinkle with salt; mix with green tomatoes. Hang up in cloth bag overnight to drain.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Drain cans of fruit, saving one cup of juice.
Mix juice and instant pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
May add grapes or cantaloupe.

title: creamy rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare the pastry by sifting the flour with the salt.
Cut in the shortening.
Put in the egg yolk.
Blend the egg white with the water and reserve.
Mix well and divide the dough into two portions; one twice as large as the other.
Roll out large portion for pie shell and roll out small portion and cut into strips for lattice top.
Brush the pie shell with part of beaten egg white, reserve remainder.
Prepare the rhubarb filling by beating the eggs and adding the flour, salt and sugar.
Blend until very thick and lemon colored prior to adding rhubarb.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for an additional 30-35 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in a 9-inch glass baking pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine cake mix, margarine and pecans.
(Mixture will be crumbly.) Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Drain peas; add mushroom soup.
Add egg slices and pimento peppers.
Top with crushed crackers and dot with butter pats. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Sprinkle cheese on top and melt.
Serve piping hot.

title: chocolate custard
directions: In a large pot, heat milk with sugar to boiling.
Once it boils, turn down the heat to low and cook, stirring often with a wooden spatula, for about 12 minutes.
Add dairy milk chocolate, chocolate syrup and cocoa.
Using a wire whisk, mix well, making sure that no lumps of cocoa remain.
Cook another 15-20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown onions and peppers in butter.
Set aside.
Parboil zucchini with dash of salt and pepper.
Cook until tender and drain.
Mix corn with eggs; mix all ingredients together and turn into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Place all ingredients in kettle and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: birds in a nest
directions: Cut 1 to 1 1/2-inch diameter hole in center of English muffin (it will resemble a doughnut). Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet. Place English muffins in skillet on medium heat until toasted on both sides. Crack 1 egg into hole of each muffin; cook until eggs are set, flipping once. In another skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter and add ham. Cook just enough to warm ham. Top English muffin with ham and then shredded cheese to taste. Top with parsley sprig, if desired. Serve immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Thinly slice squash.
Boil in salted water until tender. Drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Top with reserved cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
This makes an even better tasting dish when rewarmed the next day.

title: festive lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions, drain. Combine sausage, onion and garlic.
Cook until sausage is no longer pink, stirring occasionally; drain.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer for 20 minutes.
In a medium size bowl, blend Ricotta, egg, parsley and salt.
Spread a thin layer of sauce in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Layer 1/3 each lasagna, remaining sauce, Ricotta mixture, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake in a 375° oven until bubbly, about an hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together; put in freezer can.
Fill can with milk, allowing 2 inches from top of freezer.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in greased baking dish.
Place skinned, cut-up cooked chicken on top.
Combine soups, mayo and lemon juice.
Pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt butter and stir in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: braised pork chops
directions: Coat chops with mixture of flour, salt, mustard and garlic salt.
Brown on both sides in hot oil in skillet. Put chops in crock-pot.	Add chicken soup.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.

title: hot sausage and beans casserole
directions: Brown the sausage, onions and celery.
Mix the tomato soup, tomato paste, brown sugar and mustard and simmer 15 minutes.
In a separate pan, mix the green beans, yellow beans, butter beans, kidney beans and hot chili beans and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix all together in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; add bacon strips to top.
Bake approximately 1 hour in a 350° oven, or until bacon is browned and beans are heated through.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat vegetable oil.
Use a deep fat fryer or use approximately 2 inches of oil in a deep frying
pan.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and buttermilk until you reach a consistency that the mixture will hold its
shape when rolled into a ball.
Fold in chopped onion.
Roll into 1 to 2 inch balls and drop into hot vegetable oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: rock cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder, and sugar together.
Cut in the butter until it resembles coarse bread crumbs.
Stir in raisins, eggs and milk to form a stiff batter. Drop rounded tablespoons of batter onto well-greased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake to golden color, about 15 minutes.

title: company carrots
directions: Combine carrots, mayonnaise, onion, carrot water and horseradish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend the Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, butter and nuts.
Pack the spread into a 1 cup crock, custard cup or small bowl.
Serve at room temperature or slightly chilled as a spread for crackers.

title: crabmeat-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems. Dice the stems. Cook mushroom stems, onion, seasonings and garlic in butter or margarine until translucent. Remove from heat. Stir in bread crumbs. Add water or more melted butter if needed to moisten stuffing. Add crabmeat. Fill the mushroom caps with stuffing and place on baking sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat Crisco, eggs, sugar, baking soda and baking powder.
Add cocoa.
Alternate flour and water.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Or bake 30 cupcakes for 18 minutes.

title: dilly beans
directions: Take ends off green beans, wash and then cook beans (whole) until almost done.
While still hot, pack in pint jars; add garlic and dill.
Boil vinegar, water and salt, keeping it hot when packing beans.
Then pour over beans and seal.
Makes about 4 pints.
Tastes like dill pickles.

title: chicken-dressing casserole
directions: Mix liquids and margarine together.
Layer chicken, stuffing and liquid.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Freeze.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and ketchup.
Blend well and add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together like a regular cake.
Add zucchini last.
Stir in zucchini (do not beat).
Pour into 2 pans and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: citrus salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the fruit, sour cream, marshmallows and coconut. Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
If desired, serve on lettuce lined plates.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger special
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and uncooked rice in 4 tablespoons shortening. Add garlic powder, red kidney beans, tomatoes and chili powder.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with tossed salad.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon in heavy saucepan.
Add onion and cook until translucent.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Stir in corn, milk, parsley and butter.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: diabetic chocolate(hot or cold)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Can be stored in a jar or Tupperware container.
Use 3 tablespoons of mix for each cup hot water or cold water.
Stir well.
Use to suit your taste.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, 2 tablespoons chopped onion, evaporated milk, oats, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into loaf. Place in a 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix Worcestershire sauce with vinegar, 3 tablespoons onion, water, catsup and sugar in bowl. Pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cheese tuna muffins
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Spread about 1 1/2 tablespoons tuna on each muffin.
Sprinkle each with about 2 teaspoons reserved cheese and paprika.
Broil until cheese is melted and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, green pepper and onion in a large bowl. Sprinkle with sugar. Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Toss just before serving. Serves about 8.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda, salt, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Pour into ungreased loaf pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts together and sprinkle on top of cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: "bilodi" biscuits(makes 8 to 10 according to size)
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together; mix with shortening.
Add the milk and knead lightly on floured pastry board until smooth. Roll out thin.
Cut into desired shape or size.
Place in baking pan and bake 15 minutes in moderate oven.

title: yugoslavian easter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugar, egg yolks and flavorings together thoroughly.
Blend flour, baking powder and cloves; stir into butter mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls or shape into cylindrical 2-inch half moons.
Bake 10 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Do not let brown.
Let cool for 2 minutes, then remove from cookie sheet and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown meat of your choice.
Saute onions and peppers in 2 tablespoons oil.
Mix well the pintos and tomatoes; put in skillet or casserole dish.
Mix a box of cornbread mix according to directions on the package.
Pour cornbread mixture on top of casserole.
Put in a 400° oven and bake until cornbread is golden brown on top.

title: scallops and broccoli
directions: Add cornstarch to soup. Saute mushrooms in garlic in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add scallops.
Cook 3 minutes. Add broccoli and cook 3 more minutes.
Add soup and soy sauce.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and cook two minutes, covered, or until broccoli is crisp cooked.
Serve over rice.

title: prune spice cake
directions: Cover prunes with water.
Cover and simmer until tender; do not sweeten.
Drain, saving 2/3 cup liquid.
Add water if necessary.
Pit and chop prunes.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add prune liquid and oil.
Mix to blend and then beat vigorously 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 1 minute longer.
Stir in prunes and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crumb top, then nuts and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onion and drain; set aside.
In separate pan, bring water to a boil.
Add soup, celery and rice.
Cook these three 10 to 12 minutes.
Crumble into soup mixture the sausage and onion mixture.
Bake in 2-quart dish at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate-caramel layer squares
directions: Combine
caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler;
cook
stirring
constantly
until caramels are completely melted.
Remove
double
boiler from heat.	Combine dry cake mix, remaining
cup
milk, butter and nuts; stir until dough holds together.
Press
1/2 of cake mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch
baking
pan.
Bake	at
for
6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over crust.
Pour caramel mixture over chocolate
morsels,
spreading
evenly.
Crumble remaining cake mixture
over
caramel mixture.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes;
cool.
Chill 30 minutes; cut into small bars.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: butter chunk cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Cut cold butter into 1/4-inch cubes.
Toss baking mix and cubes until coated.
Beat milk and egg.
Stir into butter mixture.
Turn dough onto cloth-covered board generously dusted with baking mix.
Roll to coat.
Fold and knead 10 times.
Roll into rectangle (15 x 8-inch).
Spread with soft butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over dough.
Roll up tightly, beginning at 15-inch side. Pinch edge into roll.
Cut into 12 slices with sharp knife.
Place cut sides down in pan.
Bake until golden, 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze.
Makes 1 dozen rolls.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Saut mushrooms in margarine until lightly browned. In another pan, cook tomatoes and beans until done. Add this to mushrooms; toss lightly and serve. Serves 6.

title: easy microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa in microwavable mixing bowl. Add milk and butter. Do Not Stir. Cook 2 minutes on High and stir ingredients to blend. Add vanilla and nuts; mix well. Pour into buttered dish. Freeze 20 minutes or chill in the refrigerator 1 hour. Cut into squares.

title: bisquick lasagna squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread cottage cheese on bottom and sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Mix cooked meat, oregano, basil, tomato paste and 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon into pan.
Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 400° until knife comes out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese and bake 5 minutes.

title: banana sour cream walnut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and bananas.
Beat until well blended.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream to banana mixture, stirring just to blend.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon batter into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, greased and floured on the bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Let stand in pan and cool.
Wrap in plastic wrap to store.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and blend with cream cheese.
Add seasonings and pecans to taste.
Form into a single ball. Sprinkle with paprika and roll in pecans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash - chop onion.
Add sugar, salt and pepper and water.
Simmer until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain, put in buttered casserole.
Alternate squash and cheeses.
Dot with butter.
Pour half and half over all.
Cook 25 minutes or until set at 300°.

title: parmigiano(italian eggplant)
directions: Skin eggplant and slice it.
Dip in egg and fry, drain well. Place in a baking dish one layer of eggplant, sprinkle of cheese, then sauce.
Then another layer of eggplant, etc.
Be certain there is sauce on top.
Bake in oven 1 hour.
Serve hot and cut like a cake.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Place crushed Doritos chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Fry ground beef and onions until done.
Drain and then add Worcestershire sauce.
Pour hamburger over Doritos.
Mix soup and milk and pour over beef.
Put the enchilada sauce over soup mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake until cheese melts and casserole is heated through.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Burn 1/2 cup of sugar in skillet to deep brown.
Add water and stir until dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Cream sugar and butter. Add egg yolks that have been beaten.
Add milk.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder and soda, then add burnt sugar liquid. Lastly, add beaten egg whites and flavoring.
Bake in quick oven (about 350°) for 30 to 35 minutes in layers.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade, milk and food coloring.
Stir well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust and freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with lemon slices and whipped topping. Serves 8.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt and stir caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
