Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup milk.
Put 1/2 mixture in pan and press (will be stiff).
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: steak rolls
directions: Cut round steak in 3-inch or 4-inch strips.
Wrap steak around carrot and secure with toothpicks.
Brown in fat in Dutch oven. Cut onions in rings and place on top of rolls.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until almost tender; remove from pan.
Place quartered potatoes on bottom of Dutch oven.
(If dry, add water.) Salt potatoes; place rolls back on top; continue cooking until potatoes are soft.

title: chicken tempura delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Dip chicken in batter, then roll in flour. Brown in oil and drain.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes and onions; put in greased pan.
Make sauce by mixing milk, butter, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Cook until smooth.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 90 minutes at 360°, uncovered.

title: squash patties
directions: Sprinkle salt on squash and onion, place in colander.
Let drain until moisture is gone.
Add cornmeal, flour, egg and cheese (and bacon).
Make into patties.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix together Oreo cookies and butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan (save 2/3 cup for a topping).
Place butter pecan ice cream (softened) on top of cookie crust.
Pour syrup on top of ice cream and spread Cool Whip on top of syrup.
Sprinkle crumbs on top of Cool Whip.
Place in freezer and freeze.

title: caramel cherries
directions: Drain the cherries well.
Melt caramels for 2 to 3 minutes in microwave.
Make sure it is all melted.
Cover cookie sheet with foil or wax paper.
Dip cherries into melted caramel, set on cookie sheet and cool.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Roll dough into balls. Roll in sugar. Place ball 1 inch apart on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes. When done push hershey's kiss into center of each cookie.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together; pour half into well-greased baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Pour the rest of the batter over the cheese. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: zucchini meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly. Pack into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage heads and place in boiling water until leaves loosen. Pull apart leaves and cut out the vein. Mix all ingredients together except the puree, water and sugar. Place one heaping tablespoon of mixture on each cabbage leaf. Roll up and place open edge down in large roaster with lid. Layer cabbage rolls on top of each other. Pour equal parts of puree and water to cover cabbage rolls. Sprinkle with sugar. Cover roaster and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours. Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: pineapple upside down cake(microwave)
directions: Melt butter in an 8-inch round glass cake dish in microwave, 30 seconds on High.
Mix brown sugar into melted butter.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave until sugar melts (about 2 minutes on High).
Arrange pineapple slices and maraschino cherries in dish.

title: antipasto
directions: In a 2-quart bowl or container, combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with sesame crackers.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Pour over bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered pan cake mixed according to instructions and spread over coconut and nuts.
Mix margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over top of cake, leaving 1-inch space around cake edge.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Combine ingredients in a large saucepan; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: austin-lee's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Buy cookie dough and roll out thin.
Cut with a Power Ranger cookie cutter.
Bake as directed on package.

title: sausage balls
directions: Thoroughly mix Bisquick and cheese.
Add sausage and mix until smooth (will take quite a while).
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can freeze after baking and heat to serve.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until dissolved.
Add bananas and nuts.
Drain juice from pineapple and add pineapple.
Mix together and pour into mold. Top with sour cream.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine chicken, broccoli, soup, onion, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, curry and salt.
Mix well.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
If desired, sprinkle with cheese.
Half each biscuit and arrange, cut side down, around edge of casserole. Combine egg, celery seed and salt and blend well.
Spread over biscuits.
Return to oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix ingredients.
Soak 1 1/2 to 2 pounds boneless meat in marinade overnight.
Cut into strips (1/8 to 1/4 x 1-inch).
Lay strips on oven racks with the drip pan below and the door slightly open; roast for 5 to 6 hours at 150°.
The meat will shrivel and blacken as it dries.
Pat off any beads of fat.
Cook the meat until it is chewy and flexible enough to bend without breaking. Do not overdry.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Place lettuce in a large 4-quart bowl.
Top with green onions, celery and water chestnuts.
Sprinkle peas over salad.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over top.
Sprinkle sugar, Parmesan cheese, seasoned salt and garlic powder over top of salad.
Cover and chill in refrigerator overnight or 24 hours.
Before serving, garnish with hard-boiled eggs, crisp bacon or tomato wedges.
(Salad Supreme seasoning is nice, sprinkled over top, too.)

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs in 4 quarts boiling water; boil 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Crumble the sausage and mix with cheese.
Add biscuit mix 1 cup at a time.
Form into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° to 375° oven until light brown (13 to 15 minutes).
Cooking may take a few extra minutes if balls are frozen.
Serve warm.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: bacon wrapped crackers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Wrap raw bacon slices around Club crackers.
Bake in broiler pan for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: turkey rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth gradually.
Stir and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add pimentos, almonds, pepper, turkey and rice.
Stir to combine.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole and sprinkle cheese and paprika over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar, vanilla and milk (may not need all the milk).
Layer cake, pie filling and mixture. Refrigerate.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach. Combine with sour cream and soup mix. Cover with onion rings and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: spicy mixed nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In bowl, mix egg white and the water until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread nut mixture in a single layer in jelly roll pan. Bake 40 minutes; stir. Reduce heat to 200°; bake 30 minutes longer. With fork, loosen nuts from pan.
Cool.
Store up to 1 month in covered container.
Makes 4 cups.

title: berry patch coffee cake(servings:  8)
directions: Cream together sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with jam.
Cut through with a knife several times.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Prepare rice. Heat sauce. Add salt, pepper and Italian seasoning (to taste) to sauce. Brown meat in a large skillet; drain off fat. In a large bowl, mix meat, sauce and rice together.

title: mystery cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make 3 holes in this dry mixture.
In one add vinegar, in another add vanilla and the last add oil.
Over all pour cold water and beat well.
Bake in 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse in cold water; drain well.
Add onion and green pepper, vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Shake container.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: susan's favorite enchiladas
directions: Garnishes:
Additional cheese and sour cream and chopped cilantro.

title: firehouse favorite hot bologna
directions: Cut ring bologna into 5 equal pieces each and then cut each piece in half lengthwise.
Pour some crushed peppers in bottom of large jar.
Then add bologna slices, more crushed peppers, vinegar/water solution and dry peppers, layering them until all bologna slices are covered with hot pepper mix.
Fill jar with liquid mixture, being sure to use all peppers.
Cover tightly and then shake/roll jar to distribute wet ingredients evenly among bologna.
Let bologna season for 1 week before serving.
Makes 20 pieces hot bologna.

title: favorite old-fashioned fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, salt, milk and butter.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Reduce heat until mixture simmers.
Cover and cook three minutes.
Uncover. Boil, without stirring, until candy reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm, beating until mixture begins to thicken and lose gloss.
Stir in nuts and pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.

title: peanut butter chocolate frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.

title: cheese cake
directions: Whip the cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar together until creamy.
Spread over crust.
Top with pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Boil chicken until tender (can be cooked in crock-pot).
Cut up into pieces after deboning.
Save broth.
Lightly cook green pepper, onion and margarine.
Add flour until moist.
Add broth and milk.
Stir until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper (lightly).
Add cheeses; cook slowly.
Add chicken pieces.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate chess squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; spread in 13 x 9 pan. Soften butter and cream cheese mix; slowly add sugar.
Spread on top of chocolate mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool, then cut in square.

title: espresso torte
directions: Dissolve coffee powder in hot water; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar, beating until egg whites hold distinct short, glossy peaks.
Fold in coffee liquid; set aside.
Beat yolks until thick and light in color.
Whip the cream until stiff; blend in liqueur all at once.
Fold whites, yolks and cream together.
Pour into pan on top of crust.
Cover and freeze until firm (8 hours or longer).
Serves 12 to 14.

title: brown velvet frosting(chocolate)
directions: Melt chips.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Cool 5 minutes.
Blend in sour cream, vanilla and salt.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar until smooth and creamy.
Makes 2 2/3 cups frosting.

title: party coffeecake(may be prepared ahead of time.)
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly in large bowl with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Beat in sour cream, then dry ingredients, which have been sifted together 3 times.
Blend in lemon juice, vanilla and almond flavorings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Add dry spaghetti sauce mix and mix well with beef.
Add tomato sauce and stir to blend.
Remove from heat.
Put beef mixture evenly in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine sour cream and Mozzarella cheese and spread over beef mixture, making certain to spread to sides of pan.
Put crescent rolls on top to make a crust, piecing if necessary.
Combine melted butter and Parmesan cheese and using a pastry brush, brush top of rolls with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until rolls turn golden brown and cheese melts.

title: apple chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: honey bubble ring
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces; dip each piece halfway into honey mixture.
Layer in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Invert pan onto a serving platter.

title: scotch crispies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Stir until creamy.
Put in large bowl and add Rice Krispies.
Press into an aluminum foil-lined 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: hot crabmeat spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse, drain and flake crabmeat; remove all shell fragments.
Stir softened cream cheese.
Add milk and Worcestershire; mix thoroughly.
Mix in green onions.
Add crabmeat to mixture.
Spray an 8-inch Pyrex or ceramic baking dish with Pam.
Put mixture in a dish.
Spread evenly and top with slivered almonds.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve with crackers.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onion rings in a large container with a tight-fitting lid. Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, using high heat. Pour hot mixture over cabbage and onions. Cool. Cover and refrigerate. Will keep up to 3 weeks. Best after 3 days marinating.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine raw meat, 4 ounces of tomato sauce and all the remaining ingredient, except the Mozzarella cheese together.
Form a large ball and then roll out the meat mixture flat and long like a jelly roll.
Sprinkle 3/4 of the Mozzarella cheese over the top of the flatten meat mixture.
Then roll it up like a jelly roll folding the sides to seal the cheese in until you have a loaf. Place in 1 1/2-quart loaf baking dish (uncovered) in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over and sprinkle remaining cheese on top during the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: buttery pound cake
directions: Oil pan; sprinkle flour in pan and heat pan and oven to 350°. Mix sugar and butter with mixer; pour vanilla flavoring in milk. Alternate flour and milk, mixing as you alternate.
Put egg yolks in the batter and beat egg whites in a bowl.
Fold in the egg whites; mix batter for about 30 seconds, adding baking powder. Remove heated pan from oven and pour in batter.
Let cake cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pie filling mix. Beat with wire whisk
until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping, pecans, gingersnaps, pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and let stand about 10 minutes to soften before serving.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine next 4 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and orange juice, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in flavoring and orange rind. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cake in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: cheddary chicken pot pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine soup, 1/2 cup of milk, onion, cream cheese, celery, carrots, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Cook and stir until mixture is hot and cream cheese is melted.
Stir in the chicken and broccoli; heat through.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
In a medium bowl, combine the egg, oil and remaining milk.
Add the pancake mix and Cheddar cheese; blend well.
Spoon over hot chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with almonds, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Bake 15 minutes. Turn.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Turn 2 times more.
Serve remaining sauce with chicken.

title: lasagna
directions: Drop noodles into boiling salted water and cook 10 minutes. Rinse noodles carefully to keep from tearing.
Drain.

title: cucumber with yogurt sauce
directions: In small skillet, cook cumin seed until they start to crackle and are "toasted."
Remove from heat and shake skillet.
Combine cucumber, yogurt, cumin seed, chilies, oil, salt and garlic. Chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: filled chocolate cookie ice cream pie
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter.
Press into the bottom of a 12-inch pie taker.
Spread ice cream over top of cookies. Pour fudge topping in an even layer over ice cream.
Spread whipped topping over fudge topping.
Garnish with chocolate curls or cookies, if desired.
Put in freezer for two hours.
Serve with server/sliver utensil.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Spread the mixture on inside and top of bun.
Fill sandwich with ham and Swiss cheese.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan in a 350 degree oven.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry onions and bacon together. Boil potatoes until tender. Place in crock-pot. Add onions and bacon. Add sour cream and milk and salt for seasoning. Cook for about 1 hour.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add all ingredients except soup mix.
Simmer one hour.
Add soup mix and cook 30 minutes.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Add pineapple and pie filling.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until set.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Top with nuts.

title: grannie's peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter and beat together with sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.

title: baked chicken
directions: Spread chicken in one layer in baking dish.
Pur crushed tomatoes over chicken.
Next, put chopped onion, green pepper and seasoning on chicken.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: aztec quiche
directions: For the freezer:
Spread the Monterey Jack cheese and half the Cheddar over the bottom of the pie shell.
Sprinkle diced chilies over cheeses.
Stir together in a bowl the half and half, eggs and seasonings.
Pour carefully into the pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar.
Cover the pie with foil and freeze (optional).

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel, cook and mash all potatoes.
Beat in with electric mixer, sour cream and cream cheese.
Add garlic powder and taste for salt and pepper.

title: apricot meatballs
directions: In a bowl combine the first 4 ingredients. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Shape into 1 inch balls. In a skillet, brown meatballs in several batches, drain. Transfer to a greased 2 qt. baking dish. Combine preserves and barbecue sauce, pour over meatballs.

title: pasta with asparagus
directions: In a skillet, cook garlic, red pepper flakes and hot pepper sauce in oil and butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add asparagus, salt and pepper.
Saute until asparagus is crisp-tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Pour over hot pasta and toss to coat.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Mix instant potatoes according to directions on box.
Spray casserole dish with Pam. Put layer of half the mashed potatoes.
Next, layer browned ground beef, then layer the remaining half of mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle grated cheese all over top.
Cook in 400° oven until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chess squares
directions: Combine flour and powdered sugar; cut in 1/2 cup butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture evenly into bottom of 9-inch square pan lined with heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lentil soup
directions: In large kettle, combine first 4 ingredients.
Saute, then add next 4 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Place in blender until smooth.
Return to kettle and add sausage rounds and serve when heated through.

title: baked ziti
directions: Saute onion, pepper, and mushrooms.
Season with pepper, oregano, and garlic powder.
Add noodles, cheese, pepperoni, sauce and onion mixture to 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Put in 350 degree preheated oven for 15 minutes, stir and cook for 15 additional minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash squash; cut stems from the ends.
Cut squash, pepper and onion.
Place in cooking utensil with enough water to cover squash.
Cook until squash is tender, then add 3 strips of bacon or pan sausage and cheese.
Add egg and seasonings.
Place in greased casserole dish; cook for about 30 minutes.
During last 5 minutes of cooking, sprinkle top with bread crumbs.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat eggs and add to mixture. Add margarine, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish unbaked pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake additional 30 minutes or until done.

title: * indian stew *
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil.
Add meat and brown.
Pour in balance of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mr. mike thomas' oyster dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk or water to make the mixture soupy.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lime chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to
In a medium bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. Add chicken and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 6 hours or overnight.
Arrange chicken on a foil lined baking pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned and glazed. Baste occasionally.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cornbread crumbs with sage, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Cook onions and celery in butter.
Heat cream of chicken soup and broth.
Mix all together.
Add cooked chicken.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: diabetic icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter until light.
Add egg; mix well.
Add flour; blend thoroughly.
Dissolve saccharin in 1/2 teaspoon water.
Add vanilla and saccharin to flour mixture; mix well.
Form into two 8-inch long rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper; refrigerate overnight. Slice 1/4-inch thick; place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until browned.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Ranch dressing and beer.
Stir in Cheddar cheese until well mixed.
Use with vegetables, pretzels, etc.

title: veggie bars
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch mix and put on crust; press the following toppings into the cheese:
onions, cauliflower, broccoli and tomatoes.
These should be chopped fine and refrigerate.

title: hostess twinkie surprise
directions: Slice Twinkies in halves.
Place in oblong pan or dish.
Pour strawberries over Twinkies.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Pour over strawberries. Chill.

title: grape juice
directions: Cook grapes and water for 10 minutes.
strain through a cloth bag.
Add sugar to the strained juice and cook for 5 minutes. Pour into hot jars and have your lids hot.
Seal.

title: asparagus and potato salad(6 servings)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine potatoes and asparagus with dressing.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream flour, confectioners sugar and butter; press in ungreased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: deviled eggs appetizer
directions: Slice hard-boiled eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mix yolks with remaining ingredients.
Pipe yolk mixture into egg white halves with cake decorating tools.
Sprinkle bacon pieces on top.

title: squash boats
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Cook squash 6 to 8 minutes until tender, but not too soft.
Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out and discard seeds.
Mix pepper, tomato, onion, bacon and Cheddar. Fill squash halves (boats); dot with butter and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Serves 8.

title: wild west casserole
directions: Sprinkle Fritos in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour beans, soup, chili powder and hot dogs over Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese the last 5 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Brown deboned chicken breasts in pan on top of range in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Place chicken in a baking dish.
Top with cream of chicken soup and Cheddar cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: royal chicken sandwiches
directions: Place slices of buttered toast in shallow baking pan.
Place chicken on toast and tomato on chicken.
Sprinkle with salt. Spread thickly with grated cheese mixed with Worcestershire sauce. Melt cheese under broiler.
Serve at once.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine water, cocoa, margarine and shortening; bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients; blend at low speed.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; continue mixing until well blended.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in greased and floured 17 x 11 x 3/4-inch pan.
Frost while hot.

title: beef dip
directions: Put meat in colander; rinse with warm water and pat dry.
Put meat in food processor to mince finely.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix.
(Make the night before.) Serve in hollowed out pumpernickel bread with cubes of pumpernickel bread to dip.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg;
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; Add to creamed mixture; Mix well.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry first 3 ingredients.
In a bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
After frying, add hamburg mixture to sauce mix. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, stirring 2 to 3 times.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Mix the following ingredients and pour over cake while still warm:

title: white chocolate crunchies
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave (6 minutes at 50%).
Mix other ingredients in hot chocolate.
Spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: twinkles cake
directions: Split Twinkles and place, cut side up, in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Make instant pudding according to directions.
Pour pudding over Twinkles.
Slice bananas over this and pour strawberries over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: Wipe chicken with damp paper towels.
In large bowl, combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and coat well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Remove and roll in crumbs.
Arrange in single layers in large baking dish.
Melt butter and shortening. Spoon half over chicken and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour. Spoon remainder over chicken and bake 10 to 15 minutes until tender and nicely browned.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pork chops.
Cover pork chops with mixture.
Cook in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple pie(yields 6 servings)
directions: Peel apples.
Take out the core.
Cut into small pieces.
Put into the mixing bowl.
Add cinnamon, flour and sugar to apples and mix together.
Fill one shell with apple mixture.
Put the other pie shell on top.
Poke a few holes in the top so hot air can get out as it bakes.
Bake for 1 hour, until light brown.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Wash and debone chicken breasts.
Salt and pepper breast.
Dip in milk and roll in crushed corn flakes.
Arrange in foil-lined large baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Mix mushroom soup and 1 can of milk. (Pour milk into soup can to measure.)
Place back in oven for an additional 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: oyster stew
directions: Cook oysters in their liquor in large pot over high heat until edges begin to curl (2 to 3 minutes).
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to medium-low; heat until hot.
Pour into tureen or individual bowl.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Makes 8 servings.

title: seasoned eggplant
directions: Spray large skillet with cooking spray, heat over medium heat until hot.
Saute vegetables until crisp-tender.
Add herbs and red pepper and cook for 2 minutes.
Add broth to skillet and heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer, covered, until vegetables are soft and most of the liquid is absorbed, for about 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add Crisco, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pumpkin applesauce bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together, except nuts and raisins, until well combined.
Add nuts and raisins.
Divide the mixture into 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put juice from pineapple and oranges in saucepan.
Add pudding mix and cook until mixture becomes clear.
Cool.
Add pineapple chunks and oranges to sauce when cool, as well as apple chunks and banana slices.
Fold together and chill.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Combine strawberries and 1/4 cup sugar.
Combine remaining dry ingredients.
Add margarine, eggs and strawberry mixture.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Pour in a greased 9 x 15-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine the cream cheese and milk. Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Fold in remaining topping and spread on cooled bread.

title: rainbow fizz
directions: Pour orange juice and club soda into tall glass over ice.
Add grenadine and allow to settle on bottom.
Add cherry on top.

title: nut cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and Crisco until creamy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts. Mixture will be stiff.
Spread evenly in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into bars. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash potatoes, then add 1/3 stick margarine, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs, vanilla and flour in separate bowl, then mix with potatoes.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with margarine and pour in mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a casserole bowl and bake at 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken breasts in lemon sauce
directions: Cut chicken breasts horizontally to make 2 thin slices.
Coat with flour.
Heat butter in 12-inch skillet over medium heat. Cook chicken and garlic in butter 4 to 6 minutes, turning once, until chicken is brown.
Add apple juice and lemon juice. Sprinkle with pepper.
Heat until hot.
Sprinkle with capers. Garnish with strawberries and parsley.

title: baby food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add Crisco oil, eggs, plum baby food and chopped nuts.
Blend by hand.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix together.
Shape into 4 patties.
Fry over medium heat, turning once until golden brown.
Serve with tartar sauce.
Can substitute cooked chicken, if desired.
Use same amount of chicken as salmon.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Flavor with love and kind service.
Blend well and fold into daily life.
Bake in the warmth of human kindness and serve with a smile.

title: delicious meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven 3/4 hour, uncovered.
Irish potatoes may be baked around loaf.

title: crab buns
directions: Mix well and put on hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil.
Heat at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fingalings(no bake cookies)
directions: Mix together cocoa, butter and milk and boil (1 1/2 to 2 minutes).
Take off heat and add oatmeal and vanilla.
If desired, add nuts or raisins.
Drop onto a sheet and cool.

title: hot buttered tomato juice
directions: Put tomato juice and Worcestershire sauce in coffeepot. Put remaining ingredients in basket. Allow to go through perk cycle and serve hot. Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Soak overnight.
Add salt; stir and drain, reserving liquid.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut off the third of the salt pork and place the piece on the bottom of bean pot.
Add beans to pot.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Toss with butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread softened cream cheese on top.
Pour spaghetti sauce over the top.
Then spread browned ground beef on top of sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
(Great to take to potluck dinners.)

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Cut 1 can biscuits in quarters and place in bottom of pan.
Pour melted butter over biscuits.
Mix cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle over.
Repeat.
Bake until done, using biscuit directions.
(May have to cook a little longer.)

title: slush punch
directions: Freeze in gallon bags. Add 3 bottles (1 liter) ginger ale to frozen gallons at least one hour before serving.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine rice, marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Whip cream, gradually adding sugar and vanilla.
Fold in rice mixture.
Chill. Garnish with cherries.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Cook slowly until mixture comes to a soft boil.
Add peppers to taste when cooking.
Put in pint cans and serve with chips.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well with sugar.
Add salt and then add corn syrup and melted butter.
Arrange pecans in bottom of pie shell and pour corn syrup mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix peas, soup and milk together; pour into casserole dish. Repeat layers of eggs, pimento and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: marinated sweet and sour carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in covered pan until crisp and tender. Drain and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours to blend flavors.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a large, hot iron skillet, greased with 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: quick pickled beans
directions: Drain beans.
Place in glass jar.
Pour kraut juice over beans and cover loosely.
Let stand at room temperature for 3 days.

title: broccoli-cheese bake
directions: Beat eggs slightly with a fork. Beat in cheese, flour, salt and onion powder. Stir in broccoli and water chestnuts. Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until mixture is firm. Serves 8.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix well and chill, then serve on a leaf of lettuce.
Serves 10.

title: jiffy chocolate chews
directions: Boil for 1 minute the margarine, milk and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Remove from stove; stirring continually, drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. (If sugar, milk and margarine cooks too long, candy is crumbly.)

title: italian coconut cake
directions: Cream
together
sugar,
egg
yolks, oil and margarine. Sift in	flour and baking soda.	Add buttermilk and vanilla to batter and
mix well.
Add coconut, nuts and raisins.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) layer pans or 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pick-ups
directions: Let Karo and sugar come to a boil.
Add peanut butter and cornflakes.
Drop on wax paper.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Combine sugar, water and honey in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook until it reaches soft ball stage of 325° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Dip pecans in sugar mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: oriental chicken wings(makes 40 wings)
directions: Mix together marinade.
Put wings in pan.
Cover with mixture and marinate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Turn often.
To make them extra crispy, put them under broiler for about 10 minutes.

title: cheese cookie snacks
directions: Stir together cheese and butter until blended. Stir in flour and salt. Blend well. Stir in cereal (dough will be stiff). Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on an ungreased baking sheet 2-inches apart. Flatten cookies to 1/4-inch thickness
with a fork. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool. Store in airtight container. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: * rhubarb meringue pie *
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Blend in melted butter and dry ingredients. Add rhubarb and mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 355° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Cool and cover with meringue.
Beat 2 egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar for meringue.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 20 minutes, until brown.

title: cheese spread for crackers
directions: Soften cheese.
Mix together ingredients and form into a ball. Serve with crackers.

title: red chicken
directions: Broil chicken in electric skillet 20 minutes each side at 250° to 300°.
Remove chicken.
Add cherries and barbecue sauce to skillet.
Heat and put chicken back into skillet.
Cook 30 minutes or longer.
Serve over noodles.

title: easy glazed carrots
directions: Steam the carrots until crisp-tender. Drain. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: microwave cheese sauce
directions: Heat milk and set aside. Melt butter on High.
Stir in flour. Heat 1 minute on High.
Stir in warm milk.
Blend well.
Cook on High for 2 1/2 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and blend well.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Beat well.
Batter will be very thick.
Add pecans and pears.
Beat to combine.

title: swedish meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, milk, 1/3 can soup, dry onion soup mix, parsley flakes, thyme and nutmeg.
Place in a 12 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Shape into a loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Heat remaining soup and sour cream, stirring constantly.
Serve over meat loaf.
Serves 8.

title: apple butter
directions: Bake 4 hours in oven.
Bake 2 hours at 400° and 2 hours at 300°.
Check often.

title: 14 carrot gold loaf
directions: Cook carrots, onions and celery. Combine rest of ingredients in a bowl.
Mix.
Fold in cooked carrots, onions and celery.
Put into quiche pan, lightly greased.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rolls and fruit salad.

title: ham and cheese buns
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into finger rolls or 1/2 hot bun. Wrap in foil and heat at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: blond brownies
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan and cool slightly.
Add brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; add walnuts and stir.
Mix together wet and dry ingredients and stir well.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch well-greased pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned and set.

title: chocolate teddy bears
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Blend; chill.
Shape into bears.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt, corn flakes, coconut, oatmeal and nuts.
Add to egg mixture.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all ingredients, except ketchup. Cover mixture with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until not runny.

title: broccoli cashew salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar well.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine the sugar and 4 cups water in large pot.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and stir in the gelatin.
Add pineapple juice, Twister, apple juice, and remaining water.
Mix well. Freeze.
Remove from freezer about 2 hours before serving and use a knife to slush.
Add Sprite or 7-Up as needed.

title: rice dish
directions: Mix well and put in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (covered).

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan, combine Marshmallow Creme, sugar, evaporated milk, margarine and salt.
Bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Add milk chocolate chips and semi-sweet chocolate chips; stir until chips melt and mixture is well blended.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill in refrigerator until firm, about 2 hours.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Dissolve yeast.
Beat in eggs and flour.
Cover and let stand all night.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll each part into a circle and cut each circle in 8-inch pie-shaped pieces with pizza cutter.
Roll up, beginning with wide end.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat eggs with whisk until mixed well.
Pour hot sugar syrup mixture over beaten eggs slowly.
Add butter, vanilla and salt.
Put pecans in unbaked 9-inch pie shell on rack in oven; pour sugar syrup mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until set.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Cut Spam meat and bell peppers into small pieces.
Mix together with macaroni and cheese.
Place in oven-safe casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli; mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 min.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan, placed in oven.
Mix milk, flour and 1/2 cup of the sugar in a small bowl.
Pour milk mixture over melted margarine.
Top with peach slices.

title: peanut butter ice cream *
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat.
Add condensed milk and beat. Add milk and beat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; beat by hand. Freeze.

title: paw paw pie
directions: Peel and remove seeds.
Cook in open kettle with other ingredients until thick.
Put in unbaked crust and bake until crust is baked.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: texas torte(cheese appetizers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
To eggs, add flour, salt and milk. Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a flat well-greased 8 x 12-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve hot.
Freezes well.
It doesn't double well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in a small ungreased cake pan.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix (dry) over pie filling. Sprinkle oats, pecans and coconut on top of cake mix.
Pour melted butter evenly over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form into balls. Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken baked in white wine
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan and saute garlic.
Coat chicken with flour.
Place in pan. Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican dip *
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Spread bean dip on large platter (shaped like round cake); top with avocado mix.
Layer with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with chips.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: southern gingerbread
directions: Add beaten eggs to sugar, molasses and melted shortening, then add the dry ingredients which have been mixed and sifted, and lastly the hot water.
Bake in shallow pan or muffin tin in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco biscuit appetizers
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Add taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water.
Cook 15 minutes.
Spread each can of rolls into 2 oblongs on cookie sheet.
Spread a thin line of meat mixture down each oblong.
Top with cheese.
Fold over and pinch closed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Serve warm.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in cake pan.
Add peaches. In a bowl, mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour on top of peaches and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and oregano.
Add ground beef.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in pan; sprinkle crumbs on top of butter.
Then add layer of coconut, chocolate chips, nuts and butterscotch chips.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: uncle terry's too-good tomato gravy
directions: Fry & drain bacon and sausage.
Add sugar, tomatoes, and 1 cup water (you may cut water back to 3/4 c. and add 1 can rotel tomatoes if you want a little kick to your gravy).
Make up your rue and add to this mixture.
Add enough kitchen bouquet to give it a rich gravy color then add lawry's seasoned salt & pepper to taste.

title: sticks
directions: Mix together.
Pour on top of first layer.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
When cool, cut in squares.
These freeze well.

title: breakfast eye opener
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Saute onion in bacon drippings (drain off some).
Add the next three ingredients to onion and stir constantly until heated.
Add cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Spoon 2/3 of sauce into an 8-inch square dish. Make four indentions in sauce; break an egg into each.
Spoon the remaining sauce around eggs.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until eggs are set.
Top muffins with sauce and eggs.

title: beef stew
directions: Put flour, seasoned salt, onion powder and pepper in a bag. Toss meat in flour mixture.
In a large pot, brown meat in oil. Add water and all ingredients listed down to carrots.
Stir and simmer 10 minutes.
Add carrots, onions, potatoes and celery. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Mix last 4 ingredients and stir into stew.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add peas and cook 5 minutes more.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix
the
sugar
and
soda
together well and add light cream. Boil,
stirring
constantly,
until
a soft ball forms when dropped
into a cup of cold water.	Add butter and pecan halves. Beat by hand about 5 minutes or until thick.
Drop on waxed paper. Cool.

title: butter bean soup
directions: Cook beans until done (can soak for 1 hour to speed up cooking).
Fry bacon, remove from skillet, saving grease.
Cook onion and celery in grease until tender. Pour Heinz 57 sauce and tomato sauce into hot beans.
Add onion, celery and seasonings. Cook about 20 minutes longer, adding bacon pieces before serving.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Mix vegetables and seasonings and saute in margarine until pepper is tender.
Add tomatoes.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add shrimp. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with hot rice.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Add chopped olives, eggs and hot sauce.
Add 3/4 can of enchilada sauce.
Heat remaining sauce. Dip tortillas into hot sauce and fill with meat mixture; fold and lay in pan.
Put grated cheese and extra sauce over enchiladas. Warm in oven until cheese melts.

title: alabama corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a large preheated iron skillet or a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash, slice and boil squash until tender.
Drain thoroughly. Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Add squash and onion.
Mix beaten egg, salt and pepper (I use a dash of hot sauce); mix with squash.
Cover with cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake in a 375° oven until done or brown.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and water until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add syrup, Jell-O and peaches.
Pour into baked pie crust. Refrigerate until cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: belle's chocolate cake
directions: In a saucepan, bring oleo, shortening, water and cocoa to boil.
Blend in eggs and buttermilk with soda dissolved in it. Add cinnamon.
Mix with dry ingredients (sugar and flour).
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Use microwave dish and add sugar, nuts, salt and syrup. Cook for 4 minutes. Take out and stir. Put back in microwave for 3 1/2 more minutes. Take out and stir. Put in vanilla and margarine and stir. Put back into microwave for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove and add 1 teaspoon of soda. Stir and pour on baking sheet. Let cool.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift together flour, salt and cinnamon.
Add soda and water.
Add nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Remove while hot.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Combine water, sugar and raisins.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Dissolve with 1 tablespoon cold water and cornstarch. Stir into raisin mixture, then add lemon juice.
Cook until liquid is clear.
Makes 3 cups raisin sauce.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Pour into casserole with crumbs.
Pour milk, etc.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: marlene's italian chicken
directions: Dip chicken into egg and milk.
Roll in Italian bread crumbs. Repeat.
Fry in hot oil for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients and chill overnight.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool.
Prepare pudding according to package directions. Set aside.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain.
Cook celery in a small amount of margarine over low heat.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Add all ingredients together and put in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine potatoes and next 7 ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Spoon into buttered, 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with cornflake crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Put that in crock-pot.
Melt cheese and add sauce.
Add those to the meat.
Put on low.
Keep warm. Use Fritos and chips to dip.

title: cubed steaks with smothered onions(weight watchers)
directions: Cut steak into 2-inch wide strips.
Cut the onions into very thin slices.
Cut the scallions into 2-inch sections.
In a shallow bowl, blend the flour, 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Toss the steak strips in the flour mixture.

title: sugar free lemon squares
directions: Combine flour, 8 packets of Equal and salt in bowl. Cut in butter until it resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle 1 tsp. lemon peel and vanilla;

mix to form dough. Press dough into 8-inch square pan, bottom and sides. Bake at 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Beat eggs and 18 packets of Equal. Mix in lemon juice, butter and lemon peel. Pour into baked crust. Bake until lemon filling is set about 15 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite-sized pieces.
Add potatoes, carrots and enough gravy to cover.
Cook over outdoor fire at 465°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, two rabbits may be added, but do this only in an emergency.
Most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: quik coffee cake
directions: In a small bowl, mix Bisquick, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter or margarine.
Mix together until crumbly; sprinkle over batter in cake pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 slices.

title: rolled stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Separate cabbage leaves and blanch in boiling water for 5 minutes to make the leaves pliable for rolling.
Cut each leaf into 2 or 3 sections, eliminating the tough section of the stem.
Set aside.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven.
Sift the flour.
Add the baking powder, salt and sugar.
Break in the egg; add the milk.
Blend and drop onto very lightly greased cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 425° or for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: carrot-pecan casserole
directions: Drain carrots and mash.
Stir in sugar and next 8 ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased, 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Garnish with carrot curls or fresh parsley sprigs.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: penuche nut icing
directions: Place first

4 ingredients in saucepan. Bring slowly to rolling boil while stirring. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Beat until lukewarm. Add vanilla. Beat until thick enough to spread. Add nuts. This is a very good frosting for a spice cake or banana cake.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chocolate chips. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes; take out of the oven.
Cut through batter.
Put back in oven for 20 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Blend well all ingredients.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Cut 1 cup cranberries in half.
Mix liquid ingredients, then add dry, sifted ingredients until smooth by hand.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: wild chicken salad
directions: Cook rice per package directions.
Combine chicken, olives, onions, pecans, celery and mayo.
Add mixture to rice.
Mix well. Season with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out 30 minutes before serving.
Stir and serve.

title: mock chicken-fried steak
directions: Mix egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, milk, onion, chili powder, salt and Worcestershire; add ground beef and mix well. Shape into patties 1/2-inch thick; coat with remaining cracker crumbs. Cook in hot oil over medium-high heat about 3 minutes on each side.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250.
Combine cereal and pecans in 13x9-inch pan and set aside.
Combine corn syrup, brown sugar, and margarine in 2 cup microwaveable bowl.
Microwave on high 1 1/2 minutes and stir. Microwave at high 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes more or until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda and pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on baking sheet to cool.
Break into pieces.
Makes 10 cups.
Prep time:
10 minutes.
Bake time:
1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Spray large skillet lightly with Pam or Baker's Joy.
Saute vegetables until soft and water has evaporated.
Set aside to cool in large mixing bowl!
Measure herb and seasonings.
Blend together and add to vegetables.
Next, add ketchup, egg substitute and milk, followed by meat and finally the oat bran.
Mix well and form into 1 or 2 loaves.
Place in a baking pan and bake 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: curried carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 1/4-inch slanting slices.
Drain the oranges, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
In a wide frying pan over medium-high heat, melt butter.
Add carrots and orange juice. Cook, covered until carrots are tender and most of the juice has evaporated.
In a cup, stir together curry powder, salt and lemon juice.
Add and let cook for 1 minute, then add the remaining ingredients and cook three minutes more.

title: graham gems
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine the first 6 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Make a well and then add egg, buttermilk and shortening.
Stir only until blended.
Fill greased muffin tins half full and bake 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter; add stuffing.
Mix and cook, stirring often, 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Place 1 cup in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Put broccoli over stuffing; cover with chicken pieces.

title: squash and potato casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, onions and squash alternately, seasoning each layer. Place small amount of soup each third layer. Repeat, ending with soup. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: rosy rhubarb preserves
directions: Combine rhubarb, pineapple and sugar in kettle.
Place over low heat and stir gently until sugar dissolves.
Cook over medium heat until thick and clear, usually 10 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in jello.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: scrambled eggs in pita pockets
directions: Wrap pita bread in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until warm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in a baking dish.
Cover with miniature marshmallows and chopped nuts.
Nuts are optional. Cook until marshmallows are brown.

title: anthony's shrimp scampi pier iv
directions: Peel, devein and butterfly shrimp.
(To butterfly, split them almost in two and flatten out.)
Melt butter in skillet.
Add chopped garlic, parsley and shrimp.
Saute over low heat until shrimp are pink in color.
Season with additional salt, pepper, lemon juice, sherry and oregano.
Serve with rice and vegetable. (Sauce goes extremely well over rice.)

title: miniature cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a medium bowl mix flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, and dried currants.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Garnish just before serving with crisp-cooked crumbled bacon.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut lard into flour; add vinegar and water.
Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: deviled clams
directions: Chop celery and onions fine and cook in butter until soft. Mince clams in blender, then crumb bread in blender.
In dish, mix celery, onions, clams and crumbed bread well.
(Use no clam juice, only what clings to clams.)
Beat egg and add pepper and Worcestershire sauce to it; mix well.
Add parsley last.
If too juicy, add more fresh bread crumbs.
Put dry crumbs in another dish and drop a tablespoon of mixture in crumbs.
Coat well, using hands.
Repeat.
Fry in small amount of oil until golden brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Drain in a colander and put back into skillet. Add celery, green pepper and onion. Cook until vegetables are soft. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for about 10-15 minutes. Serve on a bun. For a smaller family this recipe can be cut in half.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 3/8 inch thick and place 1/2 inch apart on a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: mexican bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Place bread crumbs in pan.
Dot with 1/4 cup of the butter.
Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Cool crumbs.
Heat brown sugar, water, brandy, cinnamon and cloves over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Place 1 cup of the bread crumbs in ungreased round pan (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Pour 1/3 cup of the syrup over crumbs; sprinkle with cheese.
Top with 1 cup crumbs; sprinkle with apples, raisins and walnuts.
Top with 1/3 cup syrup and remaining crumbs.
Pour remaining syrup over crumbs; dot with remaining butter.
Bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with sweetened whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Stir lemonade mix and milk together.
Add Cool Whip and stir until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and refrigerate for at least one hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients.
Cook squash until tender; drain well.
Add to top mixture.
Stir well and put in casserole. Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator.

title: sesame ginger string beans
directions: Garnish with sesame seed.

title: cheese and meatball soup
directions: Mix and shape meat mixture into small balls.
Place all other ingredients, except cheese whiz, in soup pot, along with uncooked meat balls.
Stir gently and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for about two hours or until vegetables are tender.
Add cheese whiz, stirring gently until blended.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place drained beans in 1-quart dish.
Mix in chestnuts.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over this.
Top everything with onion rings and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling salted water approximately 7 minutes. Drain.
Gradually stir milk into soup, blend in egg.
Add drained eggplant, onion and stuffing mix.
Toss lightly to mix.
Pour into greased baking dish.

title: no cake fruit cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Grease and line bread pan with wax paper.
Pack mixture real hard into pan with hands.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
When cool, wrap in aluminum foil and keep refrigerated at least a week.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine seasonings with cheese and bread crumbs or wheat germ. Wet chicken pieces.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet, skin side up.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour (if desired, turn pieces after 30 minutes).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, add margarine, sugar and evaporated milk. Bring to a rolling boil, over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, stirring until melted.
With electric mixer, add vanilla, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat on medium speed until creamy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cool completely and cut into small squares.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar. Press into a 13x9 inch glass dish. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar together and spread on first layer. Drain juice from pineapple and mix with 1/4 cup of sugar and cornstarch. Cook until thick, add pineapple and pour on top. Refrigerate until cool.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk batter.
Coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish and pour margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chocolate on top and let set in refrigerator until chocolate is partially set, then cut into pieces.
Store in refrigerator.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Brown floured and salted chicken in olive oil.
Set aside in warm place.
Add ham, onion, scallions and saute for few minutes. Add rice and spices.
Blend for few minutes and add chicken broth; salt to taste.
Cook on stove for about 10 minutes.
Place rice mixture and chicken in casserole and cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: dorothy's pie crust
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg with water slightly. Add vinegar.
Chill for 1 hour. Roll out on floured board.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on in salted water.
Remove skins when cooked.
Boil eggs; peel and chop.
Mix cubed potatoes, eggs, celery, radishes, green onion and salt.
Add Miracle Whip and vinegar.
Stir mixtures together.
Serve warm (then chill).

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add melted margarine.
Next add 2 eggs, beaten.
Add vanilla and milk.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes until it puffs up and begins to crack around the edge of filling.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; fold in whipping cream (now Cool Whip could be used).

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix sweet potatoes and sugar with electric mixer until smooth. Dip mixture into coconut and roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and add 1 marshmallow to center of each ball.
Bake until marshmallow is browned.

title: deer summer sausage
directions: Dissolve salt in water and mix in other ingredients.
Roll into long rolls and wrap in aluminum foil.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake in oven at 300° for 3 hours. Unwrap and replace with new aluminum foil.
Cool.

title: tamale casserole(easy)
directions: Line 8 x 8-inch pan with tamales (corn wrapper removed).
Heat chili through (pour 1/2 can water into chili).
Pour chili over tamales.
Sprinkle onion over chili, then sprinkle with cheese. Heat in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: rice krispie squares
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted and blended.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal and stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and cool.
Makes 24 squares.

title: theresa's oreo delight
directions: Mix ice cream and Cool Whip together.
Crunch Oreo cookies and add to mixture.
Pour into pie shells.
Refreeze.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
(Best not to use fat-free or low-fat pork.
May make Sausage Balls too dry.)
Knead to form soft dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
These may be fast-frozen, then stored in plastic container until ready to use.
Bake frozen at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked peaches
directions: In a greased baking dish, place a layer of peaches and fruit cocktail. Cover with brown sugar, then a layer of crumbled crackers and dot with butter.
Repeat this to the top of the dish and bake slowly at 300° approximately 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sweet potatoes on pineapple rings
directions: Beat the sweet potatoes, salt, butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Place pineapple slices on a baking sheet.
Pile sweet potato mixture on pineapple slices.
Top each serving with a marshmallow.
Bake in a 400° oven about 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: classic chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa well.
Add egg yolks and mix well. Add milk and flavoring.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Dot surface with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best in the west b.b.q. baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon, and onion.
Drain well. All all ingredients except beans.
Stir well.
Add beans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is a main dish.
As a side dish reduce beef to 1/2 pound.

title: easy yankee pot roast(crock-pot)
directions: Combine roast, potatoes and carrots in crock-pot.
Pour in cream of mushroom and French onion soups.
Cook on high for 2 to 3 hours, then turn to low and cook for 10 to 11 hours.

title: geri's peanut butter hot fudge pie
directions: Cream cheese and sugar together thoroughly.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Whip with mixer until light and fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip (use mixer).
Pour hot fudge into bottom of baked pie shell. Layer peanut
mixture on top of hot fudge.
Cool 5 to 6 hours in refrigerator.

title: ranch baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a Dutch oven or other large pot.
Cook 1 hour on top of stove.
Don't boil, just allow to simmer.
This serves many and is a man sized meal.
Delicious served with cole slaw and corn bread.

title: deli pasta salad
directions: Cook and rinse pasta.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add pasta and toss well.
Refrigerate. If salad seems dry, add more dressing.
Makes a lot.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well by hand for 1 minute. Sift flour, salt and spices together; fold into egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in pears, pecans and coconut.

title: duncan hines cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and milk together.
Place into 2 greased and floured round cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato salad(for 6)
directions: Cream or chunk potatoes. Stir in rest of ingredients.

title: warabi (fern shoot) pupu
directions: Cut
warabi into 1-inch lengths.
I pile the stem ends, middle part
and	tips
separately.
Bring water to boil; add salt.
Add warabi, stem end first, then middle part.
Bring to boil;
cook for about 1 minute, then add the tips.
As soon as tips
turn color,
drain in sieve and dunk in a large bowl of water.
Drain and dunk in water several times until the warabi is cooled.
(The trick here is to cool it immediately, or else the
warabi
will turn
brown
or black, although it is still edible.)
Drain
well. Toss
together
warabi
and
remaining ingredients.
Can be eaten right away.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Slice raw peeled sweet potatoes 1/2-inch thick.
Place in heavy skillet that has margarine, melted.
Sprinkle sugar on potatoes.
Cook on low heat, turning often.
When tender, remove to serving dish.

title: cherry-pineapple crumble
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: About 25 minutes.

title: lemon carrots
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat, 15 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Add butter. Stir until melted.
Serve immediately.

title: k's cheese ball
directions: Beat cheeses on high speed with mixer until blended.
Fold in dip.
On waxed paper, place almonds.
Place mixture on almonds. Mold into round ball.
Place in bowl.
Chill.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix shortening, egg, flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and milk together.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Then roll in melted butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and roll puffs in them.

title: blueberry cake with vinegar sauce(old new england recipe)
directions: Grease and flour and 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sift first 3 ingredients together.
With back of spoon, work shortening against sides of mixing bowl until smooth and creamy.
Add sugar slowly, continuing to work until light.
Add egg; beat with a spoon.
Add flour mixture alternately with combined milk and vanilla in thirds, beating with a spoon.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a frypan.
Stir in peanut butter. Cool 5 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup small marshmallows.
Pour mixture in greased pan and refrigerate.
Cut in bite-sized pieces when hard.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredinets in a large bowl.
Add enough mayonnaise so that macaroni is covered, then add 2 tablespoons more.
Refrigerate.
Best after 12 hours.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Keep heat gentle and stir occasionally for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve on buns (rye is especially good).
Makes 10 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce.
Smash the shrimp with a fork; stir into cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Spread in ungreased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand beater until smooth.
Slowly pour over ham and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: green bean dish
directions: Mix all; cover and
let
marinate in refrigrator for 24 hours.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat well with mixer.
Gradually add sugar; beat about 5 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Add flour to creamed mixture; beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: caesar salad(serves 4 people)
directions: Using a large bowl, take a large spoon and mash anchovies and garlic into a paste.
Add Dijon mustard; mix good.
Add egg yolk and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir the olive oil in slowly until it thickens.
Toss enough romaine lettuce to serve 4 people.
Add fresh cracked pepper, then top with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Wash chicken under cold water; remove skin if desired.
Dry well on paper towels.
On sheet of waxed paper, combine flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Roll chicken pieces in flour mixture, coating evenly.
In 5-quart Dutch oven, slowly heat the olive oil and 2 tablespoons butter.
Saute all chicken pieces on both sides in hot fat until browned.
Remove and set aside.
Add the garlic, thyme, basil and parsley to Dutch oven.
Saute over medium heat 5 minutes.
If using fresh tomatoes, scald in boiling water; peel skins.
Cut tomatoes in quarters; add to Dutch oven.
(If using canned tomatoes, add with liquid.)
Add tomato paste, sugar, Tabasco and 3/4 cup of the wine.
Stir to mix well.
Place chicken in sauce.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 40 minutes.

title: choco crinkles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, baking
soda and salt; add to creamed mixture. Add Rice Krispies
and chocolate chips; mix.
Place on greased cookie sheet, using 2 teaspoons.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the margarine and shortening. Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese slowly after chopping up.
At low speed, mix in powdered sugar (after sifting) and cocoa in large bowl.
Add vanilla to liquid.
Mix all together.
Use 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans or Pyrex dishes.
Let harden in refrigerator.
Cut in pieces.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 stick butter.
Mix vegetables, soups, mayonnaise, cheese, broccoli florets and onion.
Mix thoroughly, then add bread crumbs rolled in melted butter to top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and creamy.

title: freezer cream corn
directions: Put in roaster.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir several times. Take out of oven and add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon salt. Stir and cool.
Put in boilable bags and freeze.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and boil together to a soft ball stage.
Add the dates and boil 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add the coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until it starts to get hard, then mold in wet cloth.

title: temptation bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt in oven.
Spread over bottom of pan.
Layer crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Pour milk over chips. Sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool in pan to room temperature.
Chill until set.
Cut into bars.
Store in airtight container in a cool, dry place.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg at medium speed.
Pour into graham cracker crust or baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil water with cloves and cinnamon for 4 to 5 minutes.
Put tea bags into water for 4 minutes.
Pour in sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients and enough water to make one gallon.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add wieners and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: texas meatballs and rice
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls.
Cook and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover.
Cook until mixture is bubbling and onions are tender.
Stir after half of the cooking time.
Let stand until rice is tender, 2 to 3 minutes, and serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over the flour and sugar.
Mix together, then add the soda to the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake in a 12 x 9-inch oblong pan.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion, eggs and tomatoes.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix meal and buttermilk together.
Add water until you get mixture just a little soupy.
Pour into a small greased iron skillet.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown.

title: glazed sweet potato casserole
directions: In a large pot, cover sweet potatoes with water.
Bring to a boil and boil
20 to 25 minutes, or until tender.
Drain. Let cool enough to
touch.
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Arrange slices in a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex; set aside.

title: peanut delight
directions: Mix sugar and cracker crumbs together, add peanut butter and melted oleo and mix well.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate morsels and pour over peanut butter mixture. Refrigerate about 2 hours and cut into squares.
Easy to make and is delicious.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Cream all ingredients together in a bowl.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with assorted raw vegetables or crackers.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine ground meat, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 patties. Brown in margarine.
Cook onion along with burgers.
After they are browned, top with soup, water, basil and mushrooms.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles and a vegetable.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a dark brown roux of flour and bacon grease in a large, heavy pot.
Add onions, green onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic and saute until soft.
Add tomato paste and mix this well with vegetables.
Add all other ingredients except last 3.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour, covered, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and cook until done, 5 to 15 minutes.
This should set awhile and is much better made the day before and reheated, but not boiled. Freezes well.
Add parsley just before serving.
Serve over rice. Serves 10.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar, then add the flour and beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
