Makes a large 9-inch pie.

title: seven-up-apricot and orange punch
directions: Combine orange juice concentrate and apricot nectar in punch bowl.
Mix well.
Add 7-Up gently.
Spoon in sherbet.

title: maple walnut granola(diabetic approved)
directions: Soak dates in hot water while preparing other ingredients. Combine next four ingredients and process in a blender until smooth.
Place remaining ingredients in a large bowl and add blended ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on cookie sheets and bake at 200°F for 2-4 hours, stirring occasionally until crisp and dry. This recipe yields no cholesterol.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill 1 hour. Serve with shrimp or fresh vegetables.

title: oatmeal patties
directions: Simmer last 3 ingredients until transparent.
Mix other ingredients and let stand 5 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Shape into patties and fry.
Serve with gravy or alone.

title: polish hot dish
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain. Slice sausage and brown.
Mix with rest of ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: boneless beef birds(benlose fugler)
directions: Pound steak well on both sides with flour, salt and pepper. Cut into 4-inch squares.
Place about 1 tablespoon filling on each square.
Roll and bind with clean, boiled string or fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in butter in electric skillet.
Add 1/2 cup water and simmer on 280° to 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Or, after browned, place in buttered baking utensil with water; cover with foil and bake in a 275° to 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 rolls.

title: lemon pecan pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pecans in bottom of 10-inch greased baking pan.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In a bowl, stir milk, lemon juice, lemon zest, vanilla and food coloring; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter for about 45 seconds.
Gradually add sugar and gelatin; beat until mixture is very light and fluffy, 4 to 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating about 1 minute after each addition.
Scrape bowl frequently while adding eggs.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti. Brown bacon that is cut into small pieces with diced onion. Put tomatoes in pan. Add bacon and onions. Cook 15 minutes. Add to spaghetti and mix. Pour 1/2 mixture into large baking dish, then 1/3 of cheese that has been grated. Add remaining spaghetti; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Use as dip for fresh vegetables.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving the juice.
Mix the pineapple and marshmallows and put in covered container.
Refrigerate overnight. In a small saucepan, mix pineapple juice, sugar, flour, vinegar and the egg.
Heat over medium heat until mixture becomes thick. Put this in another container, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large baking dish.
Add half the stuffing mix; mix well.
Layer chicken over stuffing.
Combine soups, milk and mixed vegetables in bowl; mix well.
Spread over chicken. Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Pour broth over all.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pink stuff!(salad)
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vietnamese rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Cook celery and onions in oil until tender.
Add eggs and scramble.
Add Spam, rice and cabbage; toss. Sprinkle with soy sauce and toss.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 adults.

title: fruit punch(good!)
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed, then add pineapple juice and Hawaiian Punch.
Serve cold.

title: chewy chocolate macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon 1-inch apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from sheet at once.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and let set until lightly jelled (take out one cup). Mix Jell-O, oranges and pineapple together.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup Jell-O together.
Spread on top of Jell-O mixture.
Let stand until firm in 7 x 11-inch glass pan.

title: two potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until fork-tender; let cool!
Cut cucumbers lengthwise in half; remove seeds, then cut crosswise into 1-inch chunks.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, sugar and 1/2 cup water. Add potatoes and cucumbers!
Cover and chill in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cake mix; blend.
Work in the flour until soft dough.
Let rise until double.
Roll out into a circle with rolling pin dusted with flour on a surface dusted with flour.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, melted oleo, sugar or chopped nuts, as desired.
Roll up the circle of dough, pinching together at ends.
Cut into 1-inch pieces with knife and place in greased pan.
Brush with melted oleo.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar icing made with powdered sugar thinned with milk and vanilla.

title: froice
directions: Make and let stand for an hour.
Temper frypan.
Put 1/2 cup of batter in well-greased pan.
Sprinkle on currants.
Brown on both sides; spread with butter and sugar.
Makes a large amount. Cut recipe in half for small family.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 16 to 18 muffin tins.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add egg, oil, milk and sweet potato, mixing gently.
Fill tins and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: tostada platter
directions: Mix refried beans and salsa.
Spread on a platter.
Mix sour cream, green onions, avocado and olives.
Spread over beans. Sprinkle lettuce, tomatoes and cheeses over sour cream.
Place chips around edges and in separate bowl.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Put raisins, dates, fruits, sugar, water and shortening in a large pot; bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.
Cool. Sift flour once before measuring.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt and sift together.
Stir into cool mixture, adding eggs and nuts last.
Pour into very well-greased and floured pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiris
directions: Pour limeade, lemonade, rum and strawberries into blender and blend.

title: taglarini
directions: In a large heavy pot, combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, corn and olives; slowly heat.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil and saute onions and garlic.
Add to pot.
Saute beef in skillet until red is gone, then add to pot.
Carefully add seasonings to taste. Cook about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in cooked macaroni and remove from heat.

title: bill's stew
directions: Place beef in oil and brown.
Combine all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook on medium heat until done.

title: turkish vermicelli soup
directions: Break vermicelli into 1/2-inch pieces.
Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onion and vermicelli and cook, stirring constantly, until vermicelli is brown and onion is clear.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil. Simmer until vermicelli is cooked and carrots and celery are done, stirring often.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together.
Melt margarine and blend into egg mix.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: lightning salad
directions: Refrigerate grapefruit (undrained). Dissolve gelatin in boiling 7-Up. Stir in cold, undrained grapefruit. Pour into a serving bowl. Refrigerate.

title: minestrone
directions: Place soup bone and beef in large pot (8 quart).
Add water; bring to boil; skim.
Add tomatoes, sauce, onions, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper and basil; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots and celery; cover and simmer 1/2 hour. Remove meat and bones; trim fat off meat and discard.
Cut meat into pieces and return to soup.
Heat to boiling; add uncooked pasta, green beans and peas.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans; heat to boiling.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups cold water to boil in a medium heavy-bottomed saucepan over high heat.
Stir in rice, reduce heat to low, cover and cook until water has been absorbed and rice is tender, 20-25 minutes.

title: warm green bean and pancetta salad
directions: *Pancetta:
Italian bacon cured in salt is available at Italian markets and some specialty food stores.

title: delicious punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale and spoon in sherbet.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Beat milk, eggs and flour until smooth.
Rinse chilies and drain on paper towels.
Mix cheeses and reserve 1/2 cup for top. Make alternate layers of cheese, chilies and egg mixture in deep casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce and remaining cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions. Melt butter in skillet over medium heat; add bell pepper and onion, saute 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in cooked rice, cream style corn, and next 6 ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased 3 1/2 quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Top with cheddar cheese and bake 5 more minutes or until cheese melts.

title: black walnut gold filling cake
directions: Mix cake and bake as directed on box for 3 round cake pans. Mix remaining ingredients listed to use as icing for each layer and on sides of cake.
Make sure to cool cake before frosting.

title: banana peach jam
directions: Mix all but sugar in a large pot; bring to a rolling boil. Stir in sugar; bring to rolling boil for 1 minute.
Put in baby food jars.

title: fancy franks
directions: Arrange bun halves on broiler pan.
Place wieners, spread open on buns.
Sprinkle with onion.
Cover with cheese.
Pour catsup over cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve hot.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pecan molasses pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs, flour, salt, almond extract and syrup.
Stir well. Add pecans and pour in pie crust. Bake 10 minutes at 450° and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Blend well. Bake about 70 minutes.

title: waldorf slaw salad
directions: Toss gently to coat everything.
Chill to let flavor blend. Before serving, garnish with more apple slices.
Dip the apple in lemon juice to prevent browning.
Add 1/4 cup chopped walnuts.

title: prize winning 4-h corn bread
directions: Put Wesson oil in muffin tins and put in oven to get hot.
Mix all the ingredients well and fill muffin tins.
Put in oven at 450° to cook for about 10 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Mix margarine and stuffing in a large casserole dish. Mix soup and broth and pour on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes and waffles
directions: Beat eggs on high with a mixer.
Beat in butter milk on lowest speed. Sift
all dry ingredients together.
Beat
into eggs and milk on low.
Add melted butter and beat just until smooth on medium.
Spray
a cast iron skillet with cooking oil or rub lightly with butter.
Have the skillet very hot and place about a half cup of batter in it.
Cook until it is set around the edges; turn and cook the other side until brown.
Cook on a waffle iron on medium heat using 7/8 of a cup of batter.
Cook until the light goes out.
To bake in the oven, cover bottom of a skillet with batter, bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until pancakes are fluffy and brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in glass baking dish and chill.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cook flowerets in small amount
of water (boiling) for 6 to 8 minutes, until crisp and tender.
Place flowerets in buttered baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine soup, sour cream, 1 tablespoon melted butter and pepper.
Stir well and pour over cauliflower. Combine bread crumbs and remaining melted butter and put over soup mix.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven, until hot and bubbly.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add all dry ingredients together. Alternate with buttermilk.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and blackberry jam.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cornmeal pancakes(modern)
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir in cornmeal.
Add eggs and buttermilk and heat until lumps are gone.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter for each cake onto lightly greased, hot griddle.
Bake until golden brown on both sides.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Pour enough water into rhubarb to keep from sticking.
Add sugar and cook until tender.
Remove from heat, stir in dry jello. Makes 1 1/2 pints.

title: toast cups
directions: Trim crust from bread slices.
Press center of slice into muffin tin, leaving corners to form 4 tips.
Bake at 400° until brown. Brush with melted butter (optional). Cool.
Fill with favorite meat filling. Garnish with olives and paprika.

title: easy mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in muffin tins filled one-half full for 10 to 12 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: mushroom burger
directions: In small skillet, saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix all ingredients; shape into patties.
May need more crumbs.
Fry in butter or on Teflon skillet.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together and bake in greased tube pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
It is wonderful drizzled over a block of cream cheese and served with crackers or biscuits. It is also wonderful served with ham or just about anything. Refrigerate unused portion.
It can be packed into jars and given as a gift along with a package of cream cheese and Wheat Thin crackers.

title: old-fashioned popcorn balls
directions: Place popcorn in a large, buttered bowl.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir together syrup, water, brown sugar and vinegar. Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture boils.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally until temperature on candy thermometer reaches 260° or until a small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a ball.
Remove from heat; stir in butter.
Slowly pour over popcorn.
Make balls.

title: sweet-sour lettuce
directions: Mix half and half, vinegar and salt in salad bowl.
Add lettuce; toss.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake white sheet cake; let cool.
Mix pineapple and sugar and boil for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in cake so pineapple mixture won't run to sides.
Pour over cake and let cool.
Mix pudding with milk; pour over cake and let set.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.
Top with nuts (optional).

title: preacher salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a bowl. Fold in the Cool Whip. Refrigerate. Ready in 15 to 20 minutes.

title: simple chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove all bones and skin.
Cut chicken into desired size pieces.
Spread evenly on bottom of a 10 x 10 x 20-inch casserole dish.
Mix 3/4 of the dressing mix with chicken broth, celery soup, milk, celery, celery salt and curry powder if used.
Pour this mixture over the chicken in the dish, then sprinkle the remaining 1/4 of the stuffing mix over the top. Take some of the chicken broth and pour around the edges of the casserole.
This helps keep the casserole from sticking.
If desired, sprinkle melted butter over the top of the casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes at 325° or brown on top to your liking.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix bananas, sugar, butter and eggs.
Sift flour and soda. Add to first ingredients.
Add chopped nuts. Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Season meat with garlic powder, black pepper, generously on all sides.
In 8-quart Dutch oven on top of stove, brown meat on all sides in hot cooking oil for about 5 minutes, keeping cover on.
Lower heat to medium.
Add sliced onions until brown.
Add broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer pot roast for 3 to 4 hours.
The last 45 minutes of cooking time, add diced celery, carrots and chopped parsley.
When vegetables are tender, remove meat and keep warm.

title: mexican masterpiece dip
directions: Combine beans and jalapeno dip; spread mix on large platter. Top with avocado dip.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a
5-quart Dutch oven, cook chicken in boiling water with salt,
saffron
and
pepper until done, about 45 minutes. Remove chicken;
set
aside.
Skim off excess fat, if desired. Add vegetables;
bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients;
boil for 11 to 13 minutes, or until bow ties are tender.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Combine all ingredients and let sit overnight in a large covered Tupperware container.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain fruit (about 2 cups) and boil juice.
Dissolve jello in juice.
Add cream cheese and mash.
Let stand until it begins to thicken.
Add nuts and fruit and last Coke.
Place in oblong Pyrex glass dish (9 x 12-inch).
Chill until set.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef, pork, onion and garlic until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and break up with fork.
Stir in tomato sauce, 1/4 cup parsley flakes, sugar, 2 teaspoons salt and basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for about 1 hour or until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Add water to raisins and boil 5 minutes, cool. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Add baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, and salt. Mix well and add chopped nuts. Chill dough; drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 400 degrees for 12-15 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: lemonade chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir well.
Place chicken on grill (medium to hot).
Grill 15 to 20 minutes, turning frequently. Brush with sauce and grill an additional 30 to 35 minutes or until done, basting and turning frequently.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream gravy
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, mix flour and salt.
Gradually add drippings, stirring until smooth.
Add wine.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in sour cream; heat to serving temperature.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Starting with spinach, put each ingredient in large salad bowl.
Spinach on bottom, salt and pepper, then put on bacon, then eggs, then torn lettuce, salt and pepper, then cheese, onion and top with frozen peas (put on frozen).

title: calico cabbage
directions: Butter large casserole dish. Mix ingredients together. Put remaining butter on top and bake at least 1 hour at 350°, stirring occasionally.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in mixing bowl. Cut in shortening. Add milk and vinegar. Shape dough into a ball. Chill for 30 minutes. Divide dough in half. Roll each half on a floured surface to fit 2 (9-inch) pie pans.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle the seasonings on the steaks and then broil them for 15 minutes in the oven.
Remove meat, then cut each piece into 2-inch wide strips.
Place the Italian salad dressing in a large bowl.
Add vinegar and beat together with a wire whisk.
Place the steak, all bell pepper strips and cherry tomatoes in the bowl.
Mix well with the dressing.
Chill for 2 hours, then serve.

title: veggie chili
directions: Chop coarsely all vegetables and steam until just tender. Saute garlic and onions in sprayed skillet until clear.
Remove and brown all meat.
Place all ingredients into a covered roaster and stir.
(Crock-pots may also be used.) Roaster:
Bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours.
Crock-pot:
Low, 8 to 10 hours.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil; add cherry pie filling. Bring to boil again. Add jello and stir until dissolved. Remove from heat; add pineapple, lemon juice, Coke and nuts. Stir together and refrigerate.

title: crusty chicken(quick, easy and delicious)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray baking dish with Pam on bottom only.
Clean chicken well.
Mix soup and water well.
Coat chicken with soup and dredge in the stuffing crumbs.
Once all chicken breasts have been coated with soup and crumbs and placed in pan, sprinkle evenly with seasoning pack mix.
Drizzle with the melted butter.
Bake approximately 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: potato-ham soup
directions: Cook the potatoes, onion and salt in water to cover and boil for 15 minutes.
Add margarine. Cook 5 more minutes.
Add ham. Cook 5 more minutes. Add milk.
Heat and eat. Do not boil.

title: spinach salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Cut vegetables in bite size pieces. Stir all together.

title: black beans
directions: Wash beans and put them in water for several hours.
Cook them in same water.
In a separate pan, heat the 2/3 cup olive oil. Saute the onion, green pepper and garlic; add to beans.
Also add salt, pepper, oregano, lauren leaf and sugar.
Bring to boil; cook for another hour.
Add vinegar and dry wine and cook at low heat for another hour.
When ready to serve, add the 2 teaspoons olive oil.

title: cheese coffee cake
directions: Remove crescent rolls from package and pat 1 package crescent dough carefully on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice together. Carefully spread cream cheese mixture on top of dough in pan. Cover with remaining crescent dough.
Beat egg white until foamy and spread on top of dough.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, milk, eggs, white sugar, 1 stick oleo, 1 cup chopped nuts, vanilla, salt and cooking sherry.
Put in buttered casserole dish.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Mix sugar, eggs, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Add to butter and cocoa.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: wonderful pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove and frost while warm.

title: delicious oriental chicken barbecue
directions: Combine soy sauce, pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar, minced garlic and ground pepper.
Pour over chicken and marinate for about 1/2 hour or more.
Preferred cooking method is barbecue grill. Baste chicken with remaining soy sauce mixture while cooking. Serve with your favorite white rice.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Can be served immediately or will keep a week to ten days in refrigerator.
Delicious with vegetables.

title: tomato pudding to eat with beans
directions: Cook
in
small pan in microwave on High for 8 minutes, stirring in between, until bubbly through.

title: mama's pineapple layer cake
directions: Bake cake layers according to directions.
Cake mix usually makes 3 layers.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream.

title: a la green beans
directions: Using a medium saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat through and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt the margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle in layers the cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, nuts and coconut. Pour the Eagle Brand milk over this.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool 15 minutes; cut into squares.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil; layer with soda crackers.
Cook butter and brown sugar together for 3 short minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 minutes, until crackers float. Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread when melted.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix instant pudding and 2 cups milk; stir in Cool Whip.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place carrots and water in a 1-quart casserole; cover with a tight fitting lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High, 100% power, for 6 to 8 minutes, or until tender.
Allow to stand 5 minutes, then drain.
Combine brown sugar, orange juice, orange peel and butter in a 1-cup measure.
Microwave on High, 100% power, for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Pour over carrots; cover.
Microwave on High, 100%, for 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a 7 1/2 x 12-inch dish layer the following:

title: cowboy casserole(former dallas cowboy, don meredith)
directions: Cook spaghetti until just tender.
Brown onion in butter; add ground beef and cook until browned.
Add salt, pepper and seasonings.
Add soups and Worcestershire; mix spaghetti and meat sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Put into casserole dish. Top with cheese and heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Add flour.
Stir in vanilla, chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: candied pineapple
directions: Combine in 3-quart dish sugar, 1/3 cup pineapple juice reserved from drained pineapple slices and light corn syrup. Arrange 5 pineapple slices in single layer over sugar mixture and microwave on High (100%) 8 to 12 minutes or until sugar dissolves and slices are glossy and transparent at edges, turning over and rearranging every 4 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack where they will become more transparent while standing.

title: iced tea
directions: Combine tea bags and mint with boiling water in saucepan. Steep for 15 minutes.
Strain into 1-gallon container.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Add lemon juice concentrate and cold water; mix well.
Serve over ice with sprigs of mint.

title: aunt helen's egg nog(easy and yummy!)
directions: Beat together first five ingredients.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Easy and yummy!
Serves 8.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: naked apple pie
directions: Beat egg in a middle-size bowl.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add sugars, vanilla and salt to beaten egg.
Pare and chop or slice apples.
Chop nuts.
Add to mixture.
Spread it all in a greased 9-inch pie plate and bake it 30 minutes at 350°. Tastes delicious.

title: "belly buttons"
directions: Toss all together in large bowl; cover and let set overnight. (Helps to sprinkle crackers with the dill weed and the Ranch dressing, then add the oil.)

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling
in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange
pineapple chunks over
this.
Sprinkle
cake mix over
pineapple.
Cover
with melted butter.
Bake for 45 minutes, then top with the coconut and nuts and bake 15 minutes more.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Prepare and cook carrots in microwave (slice carrots on the diagonal or use baby carrots). In large skillet, cook and stir brown sugar, salt, orange peel and butter until bubbly. Add carrots and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes or until carrots are heated and glazed through. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and white sugar and add oil and walnuts.
Beat eggs and add with vanilla.
Mix soda, baking powder, flour, cinnamon and salt; add to other mixture.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini cheddar quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Recrimp pie shell in its aluminum pan, making high fluted edge, or transfer pastry to 4-cup square baking pan and crimp edges.

title: corn cakes
directions: Add corn meal to boiling water; boil for 5 minutes.
Turn into bowl.
Add milk.
Add remaining dry ingredients that have been mixed and sifted.
Add egg, well beaten; add fat.
Cook same as other griddle cakes.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Mix eggs, milk and salt together.
Add flour and mix well. Roll out on well floured board.
Cut and put in hot boiling chicken and broth.
Cook until done, approximately 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with a wire whisk or fork.
Add salt, butter, syrup, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: meat dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions, then drain and set aside.
In saucepan, mix soup, milk, cheese and taco seasoning.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Add brown hamburger; heat and serve with tortilla chips.

title: saucepan oatmeal cookies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and rolled oats.
Return to a boil and remove from heat.
Immediately drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: honey-dijon zucchini
directions: Combine zucchini and red pepper strips in a microproof 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: rice nibblers
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Use as a dip, or as a spread with crackers.

title: frozen oreo cake
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted butter.
Pour mix into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut ice cream into 8 sections 3/4-inch thick.
Spread fudge topping over the ice cream and freeze, then put Cool Whip on top and garnish with cookie crumbs; freeze again.

title: chocolate mint souffle
directions: Combine 2 teaspoons sugar and flour in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk, mixing well.
Stir in egg and egg yolk and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Melt chocolate in creme de menthe.
Stir into egg mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spoon into 4 (8 ounce) souffle cups which have been lightly buttered and sprinkled with granulated sugar.
Bake in a pan of hot water at 350° for 20 minutes or until souffle tests done (a silver knife inserted in center comes out clean when done).
Serve at once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients with 1 cup of the milk.
Bring to boil and stir until thick.
Beat eggs and add to the other 1 cup of milk.
Stir into thickened mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Delicious!

title: chicken supreme
directions: Put chicken in shallow pan.
Mix undiluted soups together and pour over chicken.
Spread sour cream and sprinkle almonds over all top.
Bake 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours serve with rice.

title: cheese nippies
directions: Melt shortening in shallow large pan.
Add seasonings; stir in cereal and grated cheese and mix.
Place in moderate oven at 350°, stirring occasionally for 15 minutes.
Eat as popcorn.
Yield:
5 1/2 cups.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Toss well with lots of hugs and kisses and a generous dash of cooperation.

title: french chocolates
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Mix spread, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes on medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Return leftovers to freezer.
Makes 15 servings.

title: andi's spicy enchilada casserole(easyee)
directions: You will need one large bowl, one large spoon and one medium sized glass dish.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and spread close together on pizza pan. Bake as directed on cookie package.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Spread over cooled cookies.
Then add layers of pineapple, oranges, bananas and nuts.
Spread strawberry pie filling over the top.
Ready to eat, but better if chilled.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Combine instant
pudding
with condensed milk.
Stir in Cool Whip until mixture is smooth.
Slowly add milk (about 1/4 cup at a time).
Slice
bananas
and
add
to
mixture.
Layer large baking dish with vanilla wafers and pour pudding mixture over wafers. Garnish
with
vanilla wafers and sliced bananas if desired. Chill for an hour before serving.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Add chili until melted.
Add other ingredients; when cheese melts and thickens, serve over Doritos and top with onions, lettuce and tomato.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine margarine, oil and sugar and mix well.
Add egg; beat 1 minute until well blended.
Add vanilla in separate bowl.
Combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat oil.
Fry steak and soy sauce until browned.
Stir in peppers and onions; heat until tender.
Stir cornstarch in broth; add to meat and vegetables.
Cook until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: chili con queso
directions: Chop onion, garlic and fresh chilies.
Melt cheese; add tomatoes, onion, garlic, chilies and cumin; mix well.
Keep warm; serve with chips.

title: jackie's tomato cheese twist(jackie clotfelter)
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is mealy.
Add cheese.
Stir in enough tomato juice to make a soft dough.
Knead for about 30 seconds.
Roll out about 1/2 inch thick and cut into 3 x 1/2-inch strips.
Twist the strips together and place on baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with celery seed.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: stir-fried chicken and broccoli
directions: Skin, bone and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Season chicken with ginger and pepper.
In a large frying pan or wok, heat oil to high temperature.
Add chicken and stir-fry until browned.
Push chicken to one side and add vegetables.
Stir-fry vegetables for 3 minutes.
Combine 3/4 cup broth, salt and sugar. Add to chicken.
Reduce to medium-high heat; cover and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir remaining 2 tablespoons broth into cornstarch to smooth paste.
Add to chicken and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: parmesan roll-ups
directions: You will need 4 large toothpicks.

title: best hand and body lotion ever
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth and put in pretty lotion bottles.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Put milk in a shallow pan, covered with screen or cheesecloth and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Place in quart jar and stir in flour.
Let stand at room temperature (warm) for 2 to 5 days until very bubbly.
When it has a good sour aroma and bubbles subside, it is ready for use.
You may wish to catch another wild yeast if your first one is not active enough or to get a slightly different flavor.
It may be kept ready for use in the refrigerator for several weeks before it is necessary to use it and refresh it.

title: frog's legs
directions: Skin frog legs.
Wash; cut off feet.
Soak for 1 hour in salt water.
Bean an egg.
Season legs with salt and pepper.
Roll in fine bread crumbs, then in egg and then in bread crumbs again.
Fry in hot fat.
Drain well.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry-pineapple congealed salad
directions: Mix drink, gelatin and sweetener in a saucepan. Heat to boiling point to dissolve gelatin.
Add all other ingredients. Pour into an oiled mold or oblong container.
Refrigerate to gel. Yields 8 servings.

title: spinach and cheese pie(breakfast)
directions: Combine cottage cheese, cheddar cheese, eggs and flour in a large bowl.
Thaw spinach and drain thoroughly.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400 - 425 for 40 - 60 minutes until top is puffy and lightly browned.

title: happy times punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add all three juices.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Sprinkle ginger inside of punch bowl.
Makes nearly 3 quarts.

title: canned grape juice
directions: Wash grapes and remove stems.
Put 1 cup of grapes and 1/2 cup sugar in a quart jar.
Fill jar with hot water.
Seal the jars and process in pressure canner at 5 pounds pressure for 8 minutes.

title: chocolate and pecan cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs until fluffy. Mix flour with soda and salt; blend into shortening mixture. Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: green beans and corn casserole
directions: Layer vegetables, then top with cheese. Mix soup and sour cream and spread over cheese. Combine melted margarine and Ritz crackers and sprinkle over top of soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash and clean chicken.
Use a clean mixing bowl to season chicken.
Baste chicken with butter; completely rub the butter on the chicken.
Season the chicken with seasoned salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Open and stir the mushroom soup and add a little water to make it creamy.
Pour soup over chicken and mix it with your hands thoroughly.
Pour chicken into baking dish.
Cover with onions and bell peppers (sliced).
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: meat and vegetable dish
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 hours.

title: venison stir-fry
directions: Cut beef into 2-inch strips.
Toss beef, 1 tablespoon vegetable oil, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon soy sauce and dash of white pepper in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 20 minutes.
Cut broccoli into 1-inch pieces.
If using fresh broccoli, it needs to be blanched.
No need to blanch frozen broccoli.
Slice onion and mushrooms.
Mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch and the water

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until brown on top at 350°.

title: "quick" tijuana dip
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Season to taste.
Drain.
Melt cheese in meat.
Add picante sauce.
Let cook on low heat for about 5 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of baking dish.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Spread onion over chili.
Spread Cheddar over onion.
Sprinkle ripe chopped olives over Cheddar, if desired. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 minutes or until Cheddar melts and runs together.

title: day-old buns, rolls, etc.
directions: Jazz up leftover hamburger and hot dog buns or dinner rolls, etc.

title: mom's best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable spray.
Set aside.
In medium bowl combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well.
In large bowl, whisk egg whites, egg, sugar, applesauce, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until just blended.
Do not overmix.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake until just set; toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Place pan on wire rack. Cool for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pack in foil pans about 1-inch deep and place in freezer.
Keeps a long time.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Let cool.
Crumble half of cake in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Mix pineapple, pie filling and pecans.
Pour half mixture over cake in punch bowl. Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Pour half of pudding over pineapple mixture in punch bowl.
Repeat layering.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and coconut.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Combine rice, green pepper, onion, chicken, French dressing and Tabasco.
Toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly (overnight if possible). Cut eggs in half.
Combine yolks in small bowl with balance of ingredients.
Refill egg whites.
Arrange lettuce in salad bowl. Mound rice in center.
Arrange stuffed eggs on top.

title: down east blueberry pie
directions: Cook 1 cup of blueberries with sugar and 1/2 cup of water until soft.
Make paste of flour, salt and 1/2 cup of water; add to cooked berries.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Add to uncooked berries; turn into shell.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together and let stand for 1 hour. Roll out
thin,
cut
in
desired pieces.
Fry in deep fat.
To eat, dip in honey.
This dough can be used for fried pies.

title: fat-free pumpkin raisin cake
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients and raisins.
In medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
If desired, serve with Fat-Free Yogurt Cream Sauce. Makes 16 servings.

title: garden vegetable bake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, mix all ingredients; toss thoroughly.
Cover with foil in which holes have been punched. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until all vegetables are tender.
Remove foil in the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: spinach casserole *
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Saute onion in oleo.
Add onions to spinach and other ingredients except artichokes which have been cut in half and lined in a 3-quart casserole.
Pour spinach mixture over artichokes and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 16.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas until tender, but still bright green in color. Drain and cool.
Mix the remaining ingredients with peas, adding enough Miracle Whip to hold the mixture together.
Salt to taste. Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning and spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lettuce, black olives and cheese.
Top with onions, mushrooms and peppers if desired.
Buy a bag of tortilla chips and dip in.

title: diet raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins, boiling water, salt, cornstarch, orange juice and lemon juice; cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add Equal and lemon rind.
Pour into uncooked crust.
Top with lattice crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until crust is done.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To serve:
use 1/3 cup of mix with hot water in regular cup size.

title: duck and sauerkraut
directions: Parboil breasts.
Place sauerkraut in casserole.
Arrange breasts over kraut.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: hot dip
directions: Spread drained chillies thinly in 10 x 6 baking dish. Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top of chillies.
Beat eggs. Add milk and heat together with eggs.
Pour eggs and milk over chillies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Use garlic salt to season.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Add rice and beef consomme. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover casserole dish while baking.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and cream cheese, gradually adding sugar.
Beating well at medium speed, add eggs.
Beat well after each egg.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring until well blended.

title: hot buttered rum mix
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat together softened butter or margarine, brown sugar, powdered sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon until well combined.
Beat in the softened ice cream.
Turn mixture into a 4-cup freezer container.
Seal and freeze.
(Mixture will not freeze solid.)
Makes about 4 cups of mix.

title: veggie pita pizzas
directions: Split each pita bread round horizontally so you have four rounds.
Place rounds on baking sheet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until dry and crisp.
Spread each round with tomato sauce.
Arrange vegetables on top.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 450° oven about 5 minutes or until cheese melts and pizzas are heated through.

title: spring temptation
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet, stirring until melted.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Then add Cool Whip, pineapple and marshmallows.
Freeze until firm.
Serve with graham crackers on the side, as you would with a dip.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meats, bread crumbs, milk, seasonings and egg together. Put in a well-greased loaf pan.
Lay strips of bacon across the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Melt butter in iron skillet.
Add sugar mixture and mix lightly. Combine beaten egg yolks and milk; add to mixture, stirring constantly. Cook slowly until thick. Add vanilla and blend well.
Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with stiffly beaten egg whites. Brown in oven.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage until brown and drain.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Chill until cool.
Make into 3/4-inch balls.
Dip in flour and beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until brown. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: meatballs and spaghetti
directions: Mix well into meat.
Add eggs and milk; mix thoroughly. Lightly roll mix into balls. Brown in oil before adding to sauce.

title: miracle fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and salt in a 4-quart mixing bowl. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir until well blended. Microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes until mixture boils and forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Fold in marshmallow cream and vanilla until well blended. Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.
Top each square with a walnut half.

title: dirt cake(served at awards party for swimming)
directions: Mix pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Mix pudding and cream cheese mixtures together. Use 8-inch flowerpot.
Line bottom with wax paper.
Layer Oreos and pudding.
End with Oreos.
Add plastic flowers and serve with a hand shovel.

title: aunt bernice's stolen delight
directions: Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add and mix milk and peanut butter.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Put in a chocolate cookie pie shell and freeze 2 hours to overnight.
Before serving, cut into pieces and top each piece with a spoonful of Sander's fudge sauce that has been heated.

title: spaghetti chop
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
In skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, salt and seasoning salt. Cook until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. When spaghetti is cooked, drain and return to skillet.
Add beef mixture, soup and ketchup.
Mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: exotic cooler
directions: Cut the fruits into thin slices.
Add wine and sugar.
Pour in carbonated water.
Stir well.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: In a 2-quart bean pot, combine onion and all other ingredients. Stir well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour (the last 15 minutes of baking time, remove lid).

title: cabbage, carrot and raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; toss well.
Cover; chill for at least 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings (about 73 calories per 1/2-cup serving).

title: betty's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in tap water added in buttermilk.
Work shortening into flour, soda and sugar.
Add milk and yeast.
Turn onto floured surface, roll out dough and cut out biscuits.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Bake pie shells according to package.
Chop pecans and bake on cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes.
In large mixing bowl, mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar until completely creamed.
Add vanilla.
Fold in 12 ounce Cool Whip.
In baked pie shells, layer with pecans, then cream cheese mixture.
Top with favorite pie filling and 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Chill for 30 minutes, slice and serve.

title: tropical delight
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add all fruits that have been well drained.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: grandma stillman's coffee cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg, sour milk and baking soda.
To this mixture, add sifted flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir only until well blended.
Pour batter into greased or buttered small loaf pans (2 x 2 1/2 x 6-inch).
Sprinkle top of each loaf with a cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Press pecan halves onto surface of loaves.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: frig (sweet) pickles
directions: Bring to a boil.
Put in gallon jugs and put in refrigerator. Ready to eat in 2 to 3 days.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries and sugar in small amount of water until all of berries are open.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water. Dissolve cherry jello in 1 cup boiling water, then add 1 cup cold water.
Mix all together and stir once or twice while congealing.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, stir together all the cake ingredients until moist. Beat by hand for 2 minutes. Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray. Pour batter into pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, and mix well. Put in a buttered casserole dish and sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple butter
directions: In large saucepan, cook apples in cider until tender, stirring occasionally.
When tender, process apples through a sieve or food mill.
Measure 6 cups of pulp into same pot.
Stir in sugar and spices.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, to prevent scorching.
Cook about 1 hour or until very thick.
Pour hot into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
For longer storage, process pint jars in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: rice krispie caramel bars
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter, caramels and sweetened condensed milk in microwave.
On stove, melt 1/2 cup butter and marshmallows.
Add cereal.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour into greased pan.

title: dutch fritters
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in scalded milk.
Use a large 1 1/2 gallon
bowl.
Add
margarine.
In
a
separate
bowl, mix yeast and warm water. Add yeast mixture and eggs to milk.
Mix with a wire mixer.
Add flour until dough is still soft enough to spoon into
hot
oil,
but not too runny.
Let raise until doubled in size.
Spoon
into hot oil, about 370°.
Ladle out of hot
oil when
evenly browned onto old paper bags or paper towels.
Roll in granulated or powdered sugar.

title: busy lady pie
directions: In 9 x 14-inch pan, add peaches with juice.
Add dry cake mix. Top with butter; cut into pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix together. Store unused in fridge.

title: company fish casserole or "let's make the family feel special
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Separate fillets; cut and piece together to make eight 6 x 2 1/2-inch strips.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to reserved mushroom liquid to make 1 1/2 cups total liquid; set aside.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger in a large skillet.
Add 2 cans of tomato sauce and season with oregano to taste.
Cook noodles according to directions; then drain.

title: praline squares
directions: Arrange crackers 1 layer deep on ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Place butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir constantly for 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts and mix well.
Spoon mixture over crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and let stand 2 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Chill jello until firm around edges, then beat until fluffy with salad dressing, horseradish and mustard.
Fold rest of ingredients in order given.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Sprinkle taco mix on meat.
Add 2 cans of beans.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.
While hot, alternate with layers of meat, cheese and sour cream; repeat with cheese on the top layer last.
Bake at 300° until hot throughout.

title: clipper chowder
directions: Drain tuna and break into large pieces.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, add milk and bouillon gradually to onion and celery mixture and cook, until thick, stirring constantly. Add cheese and tuna; heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine egg and ketchup; stir in cheese, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, salt, thyme and pepper.
Add ground beef or pork; mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until done.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine sugar, flour, and 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Heat on low heat until sugar melts.
Stir in pineapple chunks and Cheddar cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut, and refrigerate overnight.
Add coconut before serving.
(Quick and easy.)

title: under the sea salad(old recipe)
directions: Dissolve 1 package orange jello in 1 cup hot water; mix in 1/2 pound marshmallows, cut up or use small ones.
Use 1 cup whipped cream, 3/4 cup mayonnaise, 1 small package Philadelphia cream cheese (be sure and have cream cheese soft) and 1 can drained, crushed pineapple.
Let this jell until firm.
Place in refrigerator.
Dissolve 1 package lime jello as directed, then just before it jells, pour over other mixture.
Refrigerate and jell.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and sprinkle with salt. Let stand 30 minutes and drain. Combine sour cream, vinegar, tabasco sauce, chives, dill seed and pepper. Pour over cucumbers and chill.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together (except sugar).
Let yeast mixture stand in warm place until yeast is lively and bubbles up. Add Crisco to dry ingredients, then butter and yeast mixture. Roll out and cut rolls into desired shape and size.
Place on greased baking sheet; cover with damp towel or waxed paper for 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: You will need pint jars and seals.

title: hershey's chocolate syrup
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar in microwave-safe dish; add hot water and mix well.
Cook in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes on High, stirring after 2 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla and stir.
Let cool and pour into container and store in refrigerator.
You may also cook on stove top.
Bring mixture to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and let cool.
Pour into container. Makes 2 cups.
You may double this recipe.

title: sweet chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour with sugar, salt, cream of tartar, soda and cinnamon. Cream butter to soften.
Add flour mixture, milk and vanilla.
Mix until all flour is moistened, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Pour batter into a 10-inch tube pan already greased and floured.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and top with glaze and coconut.

title: ripe olive resotti
directions: Melt oleo; add onion and celery and saute gently several minutes.
Add rice and stir until well coated with oleo and deep golden color (but not brown).
Add consomme, water, salt and pepper.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Fold in sliced ripe olives and cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serves 8.
Delicious served with steak.

title: rainbow jello mold
directions: Mix each jello separately, using 3/4 cup hot water and 3/4 cup cold water for each.
Set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put 1 cup pecans in each unbaked pie shell.
Mix the other ingredients and pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° until done. Makes two pies.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Fry bacon until very crispy.
Remove bacon from pan.
Saute onion in bacon grease until done.
Drain pork and beans, then add them to bacon grease and onion.
Add mustard and crumbled bacon to beans and heat.

title: moist-ever carrot bars
directions: Combine in order given.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: In a large bowl combine cocoa and baking soda; blend in 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Add boiling water and stir until well blended.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining margarine.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir by hand until well blended.
Fold in pecans and chocolate chunks.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from side.
Do not overbake.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: six layer salad
directions: Layer in order listed; do not toss.
Marinate in bowl overnight.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown chopped onions, celery and garlic in a skillet.
Then mix all ingredients together, adding the bacon last.
Place in a baking dish and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Makes large servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a Bundt baking pan.
Mix sugars and cinnamon in a bowl. Quarter biscuits and roll in sugar mixture.
Layer into greased pan.
After all pieces are coated and in pan, bring butter and remaining mixture to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until done.
Turn out on plate and store covered.
To serve, pull off in pieces to eat.

title: rigatoni casserole
directions: Brown first 6 ingredients all in skillet; drain well.
Cook rigatoni pasta; drain.
Mix ground beef, rigatoni and large jar of Ragu spaghetti sauce.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
Add marshmallows.
Set aside. Bring to a boil cocoa, oleo, shortening and cola.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add the buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Mix by hand.
Do not beat with a mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
If chocolate cakes are baked too long, they may become too dry, so bake just until done. Frost with Coca-Cola Icing.

title: strawberry-orange marmalade
directions: Prepare fruit.
Stem and mash one layer at a time.
Measure 1 1/4 cups into large bowl.
Finely grind about 1/2 pound unpeeled rhubarb.
Add to it 1/2 cup strawberries.
Mix sugar into fruit. Stir well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice to fruit pectin in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Add to fruit.
Stir 3 minutes. Ladle quickly into scalded containers.
Cover at once with tight lids.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Store in freezer. Small amount may be covered and stored in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
Makes about 5 to 8 containers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin, spices, salt and milk. Add egg last. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 15 minutes at 425 degrees. Reduce heat and bake another 50 minutes.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Mix and cook all ingredients in microwave in safe dish for 16 to 18 minutes, turning dish every 4 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend 30 seconds to mix. Scrape down sides and blend for 1 minute more.
Let cool until thickened.
Is equivalent to a can of Eagle Brand.
Will keep a long time refrigerated.
Substitutes just fine in any recipe I have made.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Add 1 cup water to zucchini in saucepan; bring to boil.
Cook 6 minutes.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Cook 6 more minutes.
Add apricot gelatin and cook 6 more minutes.
Pour into freezer containers with tight lids.
Let set up at room temperature for 24 hours.
Store for several weeks in refrigerator or freeze several months.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Put sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon in paper bag.
Add biscuits and shake until covered.
Put biscuits over nuts in the pan.
Bring to a boil the oleo, brown sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits. Bake until done, approximately 40 minutes in a 350° oven. Turn out immediately on plate.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: *Can use 2 cans cream soup of your choice.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Crush crackers and melted butter together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add to cream cheese mix.
Pour on top of graham crackers.
Put blueberry pie filling on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef (drain fat).
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted oleo, then in the crumb mixture, being careful to coat the chicken evenly.
Treat any bare spots with a gentle patting of crumbs.
Place chicken, skin side up, in a buttered baking dish. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in casserole; mix well.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pinch biscuits into bite size pieces.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; roll biscuit pieces in mixture. Grease Bundt pan.
Put pecan chips in bottom. Roll biscuit pieces in sugar mixture and put in pan. Melt oleo and mix with remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture. Spoon over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes and invert on cake plate.

title: berry-rice pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water, evaporated skim milk and rice.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Uncover; cook 5 minutes more.
In a small bowl, combine egg yolk, 2 tablespoons sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into yolk mixture; return all to saucepan.
Bring to a gentle boil. Cook and stir over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and lemon peel. Cool mixture thoroughly.

title: honey chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, orange rind, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in orange juice.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place in greased shallow pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour along with dry ingredients.
Add shortening and cut in with a knife or pastry cutter.
Add yeast to buttermilk and mix thoroughly.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt oleo over very low heat.
Add chocolate chips to melt them.
Add beaten egg.
Cool and add the marshmallows.
Shape into a log.
Cover with the pecans.
Wrap in waxed paper.
When cold, slice.

title: dried beef spread(this is an appetizer)
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Add dried beef, green pepper, onion flakes, garlic powder and black pepper.
Stir to mix well. Fold in the sour cream.
Add nuts.
Spoon into small baking dish and pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits (or other crackers).
Each person spreads cheese mixture on cracker as desired.

title: skillet cobbler
directions: Layer oleo, then batter, then fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni dessert
directions: Drain juices.
Combine juice with flour, sugar and beaten eggs.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Cool.
Combine everything, folding in Cool Whip last.
Chill.
Very good.

title: delicious apple pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.	Stir in apples.
Put
in
pastry.
Dot with butter. Cover with pastry. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday joy
directions: Use large wishing bowl and mix above ingredients together until lumps disappear.
Bake in ample pan of joy until nicely brown.
Cool with comforting words.
To seal the generation gap use warm understanding!
Serve a "peace" everyday to give your life contentment.
No refrigeration needed.
Serve to everyone.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O with mixer.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill and serve.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls in ungreased cookie sheet with 1-inch sides.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool 8 to 10 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Fill rest with milk.
Freeze as usual.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water with bouillon cubes until tender. Blend cream, milk, flour and cheese in blender.
Mix slowly with broccoli mixture in pan.
Return to blender and whip for 1 minute. Return to pan and cook for 20 minutes (simmer low).

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, melted margarine and sugar into 9 x 13-inch pan or Tupperware.
Reserve a little of the crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Mix pie filling, Eagle Brand, fruit cocktail and lemon juice and pour over graham cracker crust.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Sprinkle remaining graham crackers over Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Remove 30 to 40 minutes before eating.

title: punch
directions: Combine above and chill for a quick, tasty punch.

title: diet cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into balls (1 teaspoon size).
Place on greased cookie sheet and press flat with a fork. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs, and pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with crumbs and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Beat at low speed on electric mixer until light. Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
If necessary, add milk to make of spreading consistency.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Frost one 8 or 9-inch square cake.

title: three pepper chicken
directions: In shallow bowl, combine crackers and Italian seasoning.
Dip each chicken breast in egg, then coat with cracker mixture.
Set aside.

title: cinnamon breakfast rolls
directions: Cut bread dough into 32 pieces; make balls.
Mix pudding (powder form), brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dip bread dough balls into butter, then into powder mixture.
Place into tube pan arranging into layers around pan; let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn out onto serving plate.

title: oven-fried apple rings
directions: Slice apples into rings. Place half the amount in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dot with 1/4 cup of the butter. Combine the sugars and spices. Sprinkle half the amount over the apples. Repeat the process for the second layer. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Serves 8.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter and
marshmallows over low heat.
Mix other ingredients, then add
melted mixture.
Stir well to make sure everything is coated.
Pack
in
8-inch buttered pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut in squares.

title: cola salad
directions: Dissolve jello in juice from pineapple and cherries. Bring to a boil.
Stir in other ingredients.
Let congeal.

title: extra crispy fried chicken
directions: Salt and lemon pepper chicken.
Pour the buttermilk over chicken.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Pour off excess buttermilk and dip into flour until chicken is covered.
Deep fry until golden brown. Fry on medium heat so it won't burn before getting well done.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Sift white flour into mixing bowl.
Add whole wheat flour and other dry ingredients.
Mix and form a well in the center.
Pour the milk and oil into well.
Stir until dough is formed.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 1/4 cup sugar to keep them stiff. Cream the shortening and add salt, vanilla and remaining sugar gradually. Combine with unbeaten yolks, beating until light and creamy. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk. Fold in beaten egg whites. Add the lightly floured blueberries. Bake in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add salt, soda and eggs.
Mix together.
Stir in flour, potato chips, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, sour cream and 1/2 of cheese and crackers.
Top with other cheese and crackers and butter.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: blueberry muffins(from a maine bed and breakfast)
directions: Mix dry and wet ingredients separately.
Combine and add 1 cup well-drained blueberries.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine chocolate wafer crumbs, nutmeg and butter, mixing well.
Press mixture into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan; allow to chill.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in sour cream, melted chocolate, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
Gently fold in whipped cream; spoon into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute ground beef, onions, celery until done, drain off excess fat and pour into 2 quart casserole dish. Pour chicken soup over this, do not stir.
Then mushroom soup over this and sprinkle with the noodles on top. Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef tenderloin stuffed with lobster(assemble the roast tenderloin up to a day ahead.)
directions: Trim off tips of tenderloin to make 11-inch long cylinders. Sear the tenderloins on all sides in a large skillet, one at a time. Butterfly each tenderloin lengthwise by cutting the lower third of the meat of within 1 inch of the opposite side. Lay the tenderloin open; butterfly remaining thick portion, starting from the last cut in the center. Pat meat firmly to make a 9 x 11-inch rectangle about 1/2 inch thick. Season with salt and pepper. Arrange half the lobster pieces in rows lengthwise across the tenderloin. Roll the tenderloin firmly, keeping the lobster pieces centered inside the roll. Tie the meat roll with string at 2 inch intervals. Repeat with second tenderloin and remaining lobster. Refrigerate until 1 hour before serving time. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until the internal temperature of the meat reaches 135° to 140°.
Remove strings. Slice and serve with Bearnaise Sauce.
Serves 20.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water and boil until clear.
Remove. Add jello and stir.
Place strawberries in pie shell and pour hot mixture over pie.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Return to oven to brown.

title: new mexico pumpkin bread
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Add oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with hot water.
Add pumpkin and nuts last.
Add 1 cup raisins, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: minnie's apple crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and baking soda.
Add to melted margarine.
Use slightly more than half the mixture to line an ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Combine apples, 4 tablespoons sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Pour into baking dish.
Arrange remaining crumb mixture on top and pat down gently. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roast with cola
directions: Place roast in heavy-duty aluminum foil lined baking dish. Sprinkle with soup mix.
Pour cola over this and seal tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° to 325° until tender.
Allow 30 to 45 minutes per pound roasting time.

title: payday bars
directions: Mix 1/3 cup melted margarine and egg well, press in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
While hot, cover with miniature marshmallows.
Add Rice Krispies and peanuts to 1/4 cup melted margarine, vanilla, peanut butter chips, syrup and peanut butter.
Pour over marshmallows.

title: orange candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes in 1/4-inch slices and arrange in a buttered baking dish.
Make syrup by combining sugar, orange juice, salt, orange rind and water.
Pour over the potatoes. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until tender. Baste occasionally.
Uncover the last 10 minutes and allow to brown.
Layer with miniature marshmallows and brown just before removing from oven.
Serves 6.

title: rice and vegetable bake
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Peel and chop onion. Rinse the red pepper.
Remove seeds to dice.
Coarsely chop celery and parsley. Chop nuts. Combine cooked rice with vegetables and nuts.
In saucepan, melt butter.
In a bowl, beat eggs and milk.
Season with salt and pepper. Add melted butter. Stir to combine.
Pour egg mixture over rice mixture. Blend well.
Place mixture in a lightly greased baking pan or a tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend dry ingredients with shortening.
Add egg and liquid mixture.
Form into roll; wrap in waxed paper or covered container.
Store in refrigerator.
Take off as much as needed. Warm to room temperature; roll on heavily floured board.
Makes 4 or 5 pie crusts.

title: miracle coconut custard pie
directions: In blender container, combine milk, eggs, sugar, flour, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Cover and blend about 10 seconds or until mixed.
Do not overblend.
Stir in coconut.

title: poor man's cakes(fattigmann)
directions: Beat egg and egg yolks slightly.
Add other ingredients.
Use enough flour to make a soft dough.
Mix, handling as little and lightly as possible.
Roll out on floured cloth.
Cut in 2 x 2-inch diamond shapes.
Make a slit in center and pull one end through.
Fry in hot lard until lightly browned.
Drain on brown paper.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Blend zucchini until you have 1 cup.
Add everything else into blender.
Blend well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon on top. Decrease heat to 350°.
Bake until nice and brown and a toothpick comes out clean (about 25 minutes).

title: nuts and bolts
directions: In large roaster spread cereal in layers.
Spread all nuts on top.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk; bake on baking sheet until light brown, about 5 minutes.
Remove crust from oven.
Combine sliced apples, lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 3 tablespoons flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well and spoon into crust.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, brown sugar and butter with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle topping mixture evenly over apples.
Bake on baking sheet until topping is golden and filling is bubbling, about 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Serve at room temperature. Serves 8.

title: hen and dressing
directions: In a large pot, place hen; cover with water.
Add salt, pepper and whole onion.
Cook until tender.
When done, reserve liquid for broth to be used in dressing.
Break toast into small pieces; crumble cornbread.
Put celery and onions in saucepan.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
In large roasting pan, add toast and cornbread; pour in celery and onion mixture.
Stir in eggs, sage, salt, pepper and reserved hen broth.
Add more broth if needed for desired consistency.
Mix thoroughly.
Leave in roasting pan. Place hen on top of dressing.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour or until brown.
Serve with gravy of your choice.

title: luau meatballs
directions: *Substitute Worcestershire sauce and serve with spaghetti.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
For a gallon, multiply by 4.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Place flour, salt and butter in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Mix well with fingers until evenly blended.
With back of spoon, press mixture on bottom and halfway up sides of buttered 8-inch square pan.
Arrange the sliced peaches (well drained) on crust in pan. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over the peaches.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Mix reserved syrup from peaches with 1 egg (slightly beaten) and evaporated milk.
Pour over peaches.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until custard is firm, except in center.
Center becomes firm on standing.
May be served warm with ice cream. Serves 9.

title: sara's blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
(The batter will be lumpy.) Spoon batter into twelve (2 1/2-inch) greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot creamed potato salad
directions: Cook bacon, drain, crumble and set aside.
Melt butter in large skillet; add celery and onion and saute until tender. Combine flour, sugar, salt, pepper, paprika, mustard and milk; stir into celery mixture.
Cook stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in vinegar.
Add potatoes and green pepper; stir carefully to coat with dressing.
Heat thoroughly.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream and sprinkle with bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar.
Melt margarine and chocolate; add to eggs and sugar, then beat well.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake on shallow pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ginger creams
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and molasses. Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with warm water.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in slightly greased jelly roll pan.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.
Cut while warm.
For thicker bars, use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Put in dish.
Sprinkle chips over top and pour melted margarine or butter over chips.
Bake at about 375° until it is hot, about 25 to 30 minutes.
For a richer taste, cook rice in chicken broth.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix together on low heat until all cheese is melted.
Add potatoes and cover.
Stir frequently to separate potatoes (will burn easily).
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Put into buttered casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Put into 400° oven until golden and bubbling.
Cover until ready to serve.

title: party spread
directions: Mix ingredients with fork.
Spread on crackers.
Garnish with green or black olives (optional).

title: hot mushroom turnovers
directions: In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup butter until smooth.
