Shape into ball; wrap and refrigerate 1 hour.
Meanwhile, in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in 3 tablespoons hot butter, cook mushrooms and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream, salt, thyme and 2 tablespoons flour; set aside.
On floured surface with floured rolling pin, roll half of dough 1/8 inch thick.
With floured 2 3/4 inch round cookie cutter, cut out as many circles as possible.
Repeat.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Onto one half of each dough circle place a teaspoon of mushroom mixture.
Brush edges of circles with some egg; fold dough over filling.
With fork, firmly press edges together to seal; prick tops.
Place turnovers on ungreased cookie sheet; brush with remaining egg.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until golden.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt and blend into egg/sugar mixture.

Mix in oats and chill. Shape stiff dough into balls or drop from a teaspoon about 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° in conventional oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool. Store covered.

title: marinated salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand to improve flavor.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix coconut, corn syrup and vanilla; let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Roll into small balls.
Dip into melted chocolate and let harden on wax paper.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Blend butter, brown sugar, vanilla, water and egg.
Add flour mixture. Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Beat together margarine, sugar, eggs, buttermilk and soda. Slowly add flour until smooth.
Then fold in dates, coconuts, chopped pecans and chopped orange slices.
Bake 250 degrees in tube pan for 1 hour or until done.
Pour over when done.

title: baked brie 2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Slice horizontally and carefully lift lid. Insert the fresh herbs and 1/2 of almonds. Replace the lid and place in the center of ovenproof dish. Smooth butter around the outside of the brie and sprinkle top with remaining almonds. Bake
12-15 minutes or until cheese just begins to melt. Serve with crackers and fresh fruit. Serves 4-6.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain, slice and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs; add squash and remaining ingredients, reserving some cheese for the top.
Place in a casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: busy day vegetable stew and rice
directions: Bring water, ham, onion and garlic to boil in large saucepot. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 2 hours or until ham is tender.
Remove ham; cool slightly.
Cut ham from bones and return to pot; discard bones.
Add corn, tomatoes, okra, basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until okra is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with corn bread or French bread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lime avocado salad
directions: Boil water, pineapple and sugar.
Pour over jello.
Set. Crush avocado.
Mix with whipped cream.
Add to jello.
Mix well. Mold.

title: pizza casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add onions, pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni and sauce; heat thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Grease pie tin.
In bottom layer bacon.
Then layer cheese and onion.
Beat remaining ingredients together well.
Pour over first two layers.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: quiche(individual)
directions: You also need a 24 cup pan. With pastry cutter, cut in butter. Add water. Mix until dough forms. Use 2 1/2-inch cutter to form small cup crusts.

title: ham barbecues
directions: Combine all ingredients except chipped ham.
Simmer the sauce for 1/2 hour.
Add the chipped ham and heat the ham thoroughly.

title: the best sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add shortening, butter and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed butter-sugar mixture.
Chill several hours.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Press with bottom of glass to flatten.
Dip bottom of glass in flour-sugar mixture to avoid sticking.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: hot rolls
directions: Let first 3 ingredients set 15 minutes.
Knead flour into other ingredients.
Let stand in warm place for 2 hours.
Knead down and make into rolls.
Let stand in warm place for 2 hours. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter-hot fudge cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk, applesauce and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour batter into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix sugar, cocoa and water.
Pour over batter.
Do not mix!
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Break noodles and mix with cabbage and onions.
Mix flavor package with oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over cabbage and add sesame seed and almonds. Set at least 1 hour.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers in salt water overnight (1/3 cup salt to each quart water).
Drain and dry.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook all ingredients, except cheese, for 1 hour, until carrots are tender.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until dissolved.

title: wanda andrews' broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in 9-inch greased pan for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: brisket marinade
directions: The night before you cook your brisket, place brisket in pan large enough for the marinade to cover half the brisket.
Mix all ingredients together and pour enough to cover 1/4 of brisket.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Melt butter.
Add clams and seasonings.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: spinach-broccoli soup
directions: Saute green onions in the heated butter until soft, but not browned.
Add the flour, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the vegetables and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer 5 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are cooked and mixture is heated through.
Add half and half.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Serve piping hot with favorite bread.
Serves 4.
Garnish soup with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix zucchini, sugar, water, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cook for 20 minutes or until tender, then add to mixture.
Mix flour and water for thickening; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken divan pie
directions: Dip meat in flour.
Brown quickly and remove to warm platter. Stir bouillon, water and wine into skillet. Add juice of 1 lemon and grated lemon peel. Return turkey to pan and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until tender.
Garnish platter with lemon slices and parsley.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix everything together except 1/2 cup cheese.	Put remaining cheese on top and cook in crock-pot on low 4 hours.
Do Not Stir!

title: happy dessert "cream cheese cake"
directions: Mix crushed crackers with butter and sugar or sweetener.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine ice cream and Cool Whip.
Spread over Oreo cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: rye snacks
directions: Mix and spread on party rye.
Put under broiler until brown. Serve warm.

title: crabmeat bacon rolls
directions: Mix tomato paste with egg.
Add salt, crumbs, parsley, celery salt and crabmeat.
Mix thoroughly and chill.
Roll into finger lengths, wrap each roll and 1/2 strip of bacon and fasten with toothpicks.
Chill well.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of casserole dish; cover with soup mixture and then Swiss cheese.
Cover cheese with remaining soup mixture.
Top with stuffing and pour butter over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until bubbly).

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add juice from pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy.
Fold into remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Mix yellow Jiffy cake mix as directed on box.
In a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan, bake 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: maple easter egg filling
directions: Cream together; knead real good.
You can also substitute 1 tsp vanilla for the maple and add coconut.
Dip in melted chocolate and place on wax paper to set.
Makes a large batch.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar.
Stir in milk and bring to a boil. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Yields 2 cups.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until cooked through.
Cool, then peel and cut in chunks.
Hard-boil egg, cool and cut up.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper, celery and a little milk; add to potatoes and egg.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Wash all vegetables and cut into large chunks.
Put in pan and add just enough water to cover.
If using canned peas, do not add until after butter is added.
Boil until vegetables are tender.
Add butter a chunk at a time so it melts easier.
Stir. Add the can of evaporated milk.
For a richer chowder add one large and one small can evaporated milk.
Reheat.
Add cheddar cheese and pepper when served.
A mix of cheddar and mozzarella cheese is also good.

title: recipe for a happy day
directions: Measure words carefully.
Add cups of understanding.
Use generous amounts of time and patience.
Keep temperatures low.
Do not boil.
Add a dash of humor and warm personality.
Season to taste with spice of life.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix in large bowl the all-bran, sifted flour and salt.
Mix in blender the sour milk (add baking soda to milk), sugar, Karo syrup and egg.
Bake in 2 greased and dusted bread pans at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil last 10 minutes to prevent overbrowning. Test for doneness with toothpick (with glass pan reduce oven heat by 25°).
To sour milk, add 1 tablespoon vinegar or lemon juice to regular milk.

title: dill pickles
directions: Heat water, salt and vinegar to rolling boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Place dill in jars.
Pack jars with cucumbers. When liquid is cool, pour over cucumbers.
Be sure to cover cucumbers completely.
Let set 90 days.

title: sweet fried cantaloupe
directions: Cut melon into thin slices; remove seeds and skin.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and liqueur.
Let stand for at least 1 hour. Mix together flour, wine, 1/2 teaspoon oil and a little salt. Blend in stiff egg white.
Dip melon slices into batter and fry in hot olive oil only until light gold in color.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve.

title: hidden valley ranch buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dredge chicken in salad dressing mix. Dip in mixture of margarine, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Arrange on baking pan (sprayed with Pam) and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn, sprinkle with paprika and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Try dipping in Blue cheese dressing.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt Velveeta in cooked sausage. Add chili and heat thoroughly.
Serve with chips or crackers while hot.

title: cajun style london broil(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Sprinkle meat tenderizer on both sides of meat.
Let stand for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle both sides of meat with spices.
Cook on red hot grill 5 minutes on both sides.
Put honey on top after cooked. Serve after honey melts.
Slice thin.
Bearnaise sauce acceptable.

title: quick rolls
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: sunday fried chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and oil.
Place about 1 cup flour mixture in a paper or plastic bag.
Shake a few chicken pieces in the bag at a time, coating well.
On medium-high, heat 1/4 inch of oil in a large skillet.
Brown chicken on all sides; remove to a large, shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Recipe makes enough coating for three chickens.
Store unused mixture in airtight container. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, chopped pecans and margarine together in a small bowl (save a few pecans for top).
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 20 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Mix the cream cheese (beat before adding powdered sugar) and powdered sugar.
Add 8 ounces Cool Whip (save remaining for top).
Beat the mixture and put on top of cooled crust.
Mix milk with chocolate pudding.
Make a layer of this on top of cream cheese mixture.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and pecans.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Use on broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms, celery, radishes, carrots and green onions.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend together and add a small can finely chopped shrimp.

title: five bean salad
directions: Drain beans, mix in all ingredients.
Stir well and chill for 2 to 4 hours before serving.
Serves 12.

title: no-bake strawberry bottom cheese cake
directions: Place berries on paper towels to drain.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spread thin layer of glaze over bottom of crust.
Place berries on glaze and cover with another thin layer of glaze.
Gently spoon mixture over glazed berries over crust.
Cover with inverted dome and chill to set, at least 4 hours.

title: betsy's potato soup
directions: Bring water to boil; put potatoes in and chicken seasoning, pepper and salt.
Cook until 1/2 tender.
Add soup, simmer for 10 minutes.
While simmering, melt margarine; add flour to butter to make paste.
Add to potatoes.
Add milk; heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.

title: oreo icebox dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble cookies.
In mixing bowl, blend the cream cheese, powdered sugar and half of milk.
Add peanut butter and other half milk; beat until smooth.
Add container of Cool Whip.
Pour over cookies and freeze.
Serves 15.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: peanut crisps
directions: Blend peanut butter, Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour and baking soda.
Roll into small balls and roll into granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Remove. Top with Hershey's Kiss in center.
Bake for 5 minutes more. Yield:
3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Saut onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in butter, celery salt, red pepper and worcestershire sauce. Combine cracker crumbs and parsley flakes.
Preheat oven to 350°. Drain oysters, reserving 1/3 c. liquor.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cracker crumbs in bottom of a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish; layer half of oysters and half of remaining cracker crumb mixture. Drizzle with half of butter mixture.
Repeat layers.
Combine eggs, half and half, and reserved oyster liquor; mix well.
Pour over oyster layers.
Bake for 40-45 minutes or until set.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until size of peas. Add buttermilk and then yeast mixture.
Stir until all flour is dampened.
Knead on floured board.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.
(This dough can be stored in a tightly covered container in refrigerator for 2 weeks.)

title: chuck roast
directions: Place roast in a glass baking dish.
Mix ingredients and pour over chuck roast.
Cook for 5 hours, covered, at 325°.
When done, break meat apart with fork.
Serve on fresh hard rolls.

title: eggplant-zucchini parmigiana
directions: In medium saucepan, combine broth, celery, onion and garlic. Bring to boil and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, herbs and pepper.
Return to boil and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices and halve slices.
Bring 1/2-inch water to boil in Dutch oven.
Add eggplant and zucchini slices; simmer, covered, for 4 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Divide mixture in half.
Let 1/2 remain at room temperature.
Chill other half in pan or other container until set.
Spread sour cream over congealed mixture.
Spoon the remaining mixture over sour cream.
Congeal.

title: noah's ark clam chowder
directions: Combine in 3 quart saucepan.
Heat over low heat.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil all ingredients, except corn and soda for 5 minutes, mixing well and stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add soda. Stir quickly.
Pour over popped corn.

title: sassy spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain well (very important).
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cook vinegar, egg and sugar until custard-like.
Keep stirring.
Let cool.
Add cream cheese to egg mixture and blend well.
Add shrimp.
Mix well.
Garnish with whole shrimp and parsley.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: lehto's upper peninsula pasties
directions: Cut lard and suet into flour to a coarse crumb.
Add water, mixing with a fork.
Refrigerate until ready to roll.

title: pineapple-lemonade punch
directions: In a large pitcher, combine pineapple juice, lemonade and water.
Chill for 2 hours or more.
Add club soda and if desired, strawberries.
For an alcohol drink,
Increase water to 6 cups and add 1 1/2 cups of Rum or Tequila and omit the club soda.

title: vinegar cake
directions: Follow directions for cake mix and bake.
In a pot mix vinegar and sugar.
Cook on medium heat until it begins to thicken.
Polk holes in finished cake and pour vinegar mixture over top of cake.
Let cool and serve.

title: marinade sauce(for pork chops)
directions: In a sauce pan, combine ingredients (not soda).
Bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Let cool.
Add soda.
Pour over pork chops.
Marinate for 2 - 3 days.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and milk.
Stir in flour and cinnamon until just combined.
Fold in apples, pecans and coconut.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in water and boil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from water and arrange in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook chicken, debone and cut in little pieces.
Place chicken over broccoli. Spoon chicken soup over chicken and pour on broth.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: jinny's easy apple cake
directions: In medium large bowl add apples, beaten egg and oil and mix. Add sugar, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix well and add flour.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in prepared 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Delicious with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.
Best of all, easy! Men love it.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together and set aside.
Mix pretzels and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Spread cheese mixture over pretzels.
Spread whipped topping over cheese and chill.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling hot pineapple juice.
Add strawberries, being sure the liquid on berries does amount to more than 2 cups.
Allow mixture to start to gel before pouring over the whipped topping.

title: western walnut ice cream topping
directions: Mix together and store in the refrigerator for a few days. You may want to set the jar in a pan of hot water before serving. It is not necessary to add any calories to this recipe.

title: apple cobbler muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Grease muffin tin. Combine the quick bread mix (both bags), apple juice, eggs, and yogurt in a large bowl.
Beat just until mixed.

Stir in walnuts and raisins. Spoon into muffin cups, filling each 2/3 full. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of a muffin. Remove from pan immediately and place on rack to cool slightly.

title: potluck potato casserole
directions: Use a 3-quart dish.
Defrost hash browns.
Combine 1/2 cup of butter with hash browns.
Mix rest of ingredients together and mix into hash browns.
Butter a 3-quart casserole and put hash brown mixture in dish.
Mix corn flakes with 1/4 cup melted butter. Pour over top of mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until thick and lemony. Gradually add sugar.
While beating, add milk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 15-inch jelly roll pan or a large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread 1 cup of peanut butter over hot cake.
Cool thoroughly before covering with melted chocolate chips.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: aloha cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour
in
greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: cajun cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Stir in eggs and pineapple and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 10 x 2 inch pan and bake for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sour-cream raisin bars

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and oleo until well mixed.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar.
Heat to a boil.
Add jello, stir well and let cool.
Add buttermilk. Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Pour in pan and congeal.

title: pickled cucumbers
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Mix vinegar and sugar with cucumbers.
Put into containers and freeze.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes. May take a little longer, watch carefully.

title: easy barbecue
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Drain grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir together sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add water.
Stir until smooth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil until it thickens.
Add vanilla, butter and food coloring. Cool by stirring.
Drain strawberries and add to sauce.
Pour into pie shell and top with whipped topping.

title: peaches 'n cream cheesecake(this is really good!)
directions: This is a very good cake.
The coconut topping can be doubled for a more flavorful cake.
Then some of this topping can be put between layers with the frosting, as well as on the top and sides.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put pecans on top.
Bake in Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat and bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: apple crumble
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square 8 x 8-inch baking dish or rectangle 10 x 6-inch.
Arrange apples in dish.

Mix Bisquick, sugar and egg until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Drizzle margarine over the top. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain thoroughly and discard juice.
Whip the cream with the sugar and vanilla.
Add whipped cream and remaining ingredients to sweetened cranberries.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving. Serves 20.

title: pasta with daylily buds and mushrooms
directions: Cook pasta while preparing vegetables.
Clean first six ounces of mushrooms with a brush or damp towel; do not rinse.
Tear or cut into bite-size pieces.
(If using shiitake, remove hard stems.)

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onions in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add 1 cup chicken broth, chicken soup and green chiles.
Heat thoroughly.
Add chicken.
In glass dish or pan, layer with tortillas (torn into bite-size pieces).
Layer with meat mixture, layer of cheese, layer tortillas and end with layer of cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until heated thoroughly.
Top with sour cream and salsa.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and parsley flakes until soft dough forms.
Beat 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown in a 450° oven.

title: savory spaghetti sauce
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain.
Add the next 8 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove the bay leaf.
Serve over spaghetti. Garnish with fresh oregano, if desired.
Makes about 1 quart and serves 4 to 6.

title: easy citrus broccoli
directions: Wash and cut up broccoli.
Place broccoli in steamer over boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Transfer to a serving plate and keep warm.

title: toasted coconut cream pie
directions: Toast coconut lightly.
Bring sour cream to room temperature. In a saucepan, combine milk, egg yolks, water and pudding mix. Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Beat in sour cream.
Stir in 1/2 cup of coconut.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of coconut on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: dried beef and lima casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine and brown chopped onion in it.
Add flour and milk and stir until smooth and thick.
Pour over dried beef and cooked lima beans.
Add chopped egg white and lemon juice. Stir mixture.
Sprinkle with egg yolks.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: country fried turkey nuggets
directions: Slice turkey (chicken) breast into nuggets, whatever size is desirable.
Wash meat thoroughly in cold water.
Mix eggs, milk and A.1. steak sauce.
Egg whites may be separated if desired. Marinate nuggets in batter for 2 to 3 hours.

title: oatmeal-raisin muffins
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 in cupcake pans or 24 in muffin pans.

title: breakfast lasagna
directions: Butter bottom of 9-inch pan.
Place bread on bottom.
Brown sausage and bacon; spread over bread.
Beat eggs and add milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread and meat.
Repeat as needed.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake for 20 minutes.
Add cheese on top and bake 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until top is nicely browned.

title: garden casserole
directions: Fry meat and drain.
Layer potatoes, carrots, English peas, and corn in large baking dish.
Add meat and put oleo on top of meat. Pour tomatoes and tomato sauce on top.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: german pancake
directions: Melt butter in baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Beat eggs and add milk; mix well.
Add flour a little at a time and mix smooth. Pour in pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in crusts.
Sprinkle with coconut on top.

title: rice pilaf(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Melt 1/4 pound butter in a skillet; saute the onions, parsley and 1 clove minced garlic. Add the rice and sprinkle with fine herbs (eg. oregano,
thyme) and a pinch of salt; stir and add boiling chicken broth. Mix thoroughly; cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Spread on any platter that has a deep center.
Defrost snow crab.
Squeeze thoroughly to remove all moisture.
Flake on top of cream cheese. Top with shrimp sauce and garnish with parsley.
If made early in the day, remove from refrigerator 1/2 hour before serving for spreading consistency.
Serve with crackers.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, beat 1 1/2 cups sugar and softened margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs. Add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Make into 1-inch balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: raisin-pecan pie
directions: Roll pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate; trim off excess pastry along edges.
Fold edges under and flute.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 450° for 3 to 5 minutes; remove from oven.
Cool.

title: turkey spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously butter 9-inch pie pan (1 1/2-inches deep).
Break spaghetti in half.
Cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Cook onion, pepper and garlic in oil.
Pour rest of ingredients in.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise, remove and discard stems, seeds, and membranes.
Peel and quarter onion.
In blender or food processor, process peppers and cilantro until finely chopped.
Add salt and lime juice.
Add tomatoes and onions and pulse until they are coarsely chopped. Transfer to serving dish and serve within 1 or 2 hours.
Makes 2 cups.

title: sesame fried rice
directions: Boil and cut chicken while cooking rice.
Heat large skillet with oil.
Add rice slowly, stirring constantly.
Add onion, then peas, stirring constantly.
When heated through, serve.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Let bread thaw but do not let rise (about 30 to 45 minutes). Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear one loaf of bread and put in pan. Melt butter; add rest of ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour over dough.
Tear second loaf and throw in empty spots.
Let rise 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove onto plate or wax paper.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Mix all ingredients (except steak); bring to a boil. Tenderize steak with tenderizing salt.
Put steaks in sauce; cook over low heat for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Serve immediately!

title: hot nectar tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags in a kettle and cover.
Steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Combine pineapple juice, apricot nectar, orange concentrate, lemon juice, sugar and water in a kettle; heat slowly, stirring several times, to simmering.
Stir in hot tea.
Very carefully pour into a large punch bowl.
Garnish with lime and lemon slices and maraschino cherries threaded onto a long skewer.
Ladle into punch cups.
Serve warm.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Note:
You might want to prepare in the late evening.

title: galumpkies(stuffed cabbage)
directions: Core cabbage and steam by setting cabbage in large bowl with water.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Cabbage is done when leaves are "workable".

title: deviled eggs supreme
directions: Boil eggs 10 minutes.
Drain, peel and cut in half lengthwise and cool about 10 minutes.

Remove yolks and add to pickles, Miracle Whip, sugar, dill weed, salt and pepper, onion and celery. Stir well and fill egg halves with 1 tablespoon of mixture. Sprinkle with paprika and chill until cool.
Garnish with celery leaves.
If there is any remaining egg mixture, make a sandwich!

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and Sugar Twin in a mixing bowl.
Add milk, yogurt and raspberry flavoring; stir just to blend.
Spray a muffin tin with nonstick spray.
Divide batter evenly into 18 muffins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 18 muffins.

title: fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients. Chill.
Serve with fruit slices.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and grated Cheddar.
Add all other ingredients, except pecans; mix well.
Shape into ball or roll. Roll in pecans.
Wrap in foil and chill 24 hours before serving.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind green peppers, red peppers, green tomatoes and onions. Let drain 1 hour.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt, flour and celery seed to mustard.
Stir and boil for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add mayonnaise. Put leftovers in freezer bowls or canning jars and seal.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: luscious fruit dip
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Let cool completely.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: fettuccine with basil, turkey and walnuts
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook noodles until almost tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Add cream, turkey ham, basil, cheese and hot pepper flakes to pot.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until very hot and well blended.
Add pasta and walnuts and cook, tossing, 1 to 2 minutes, until heated through.
Serve immediately.

title: fruity yogurt drink
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender. Blend until well mixed. Serve cold.

title: taco wheels
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas. Roll up as for jelly roll. Slice as desired. Arrange on platter. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, salt, yolks and whole eggs.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Add with sour cream to butter mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder, nutmeg and vanilla and add to egg mixture. Dough will be sticky.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight. Roll on well-floured surface.
Cut and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are set, but not browned.

title: mexican round up
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, water, beans and Spanish rice.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put Fritos on a pizza pan. Pour meat mixture over Fritos.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: cherry delight
directions: Whip Dream Whip; mix with sugar and cream cheese.
Spread in crust.
Add cherry pie filling.
Enjoy!

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for 1 hour.
May be made ahead if sealed and refrigerated.
